g',0),(266,2,'2016-12-01 14:12:51','2016-12-01 14:12:51','','tanya2','','inherit','open','closed','','tanya2','','','2016-12-01 14:12:51','2016-12-01 14:12:51','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tanya2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(267,2,'2016-12-01 14:12:52','2016-12-01 14:12:52','','tatum1','','inherit','open','closed','','tatum1','','','2016-12-01 14:12:52','2016-12-01 14:12:52','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tatum1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(268,2,'2016-12-01 14:12:54','2016-12-01 14:12:54','','tatum2','','inherit','open','closed','','tatum2','','','2016-12-01 14:12:54','2016-12-01 14:12:54','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tatum2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(269,2,'2016-12-01 14:12:54','2016-12-01 14:12:54','','valerie1','','inherit','open','closed','','valerie1','','','2016-12-01 14:12:54','2016-12-01 14:12:54','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Valerie1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(270,2,'2016-12-01 14:12:55','2016-12-01 14:12:55','','valerie2','','inherit','open','closed','','valerie2','','','2016-12-01 14:12:55','2016-12-01 14:12:55','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Valerie2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(271,2,'2016-12-01 14:17:07','2016-12-01 14:17:07','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Jodie Foster</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at 3 years, Jodie had begun her acting career. At 5 years, she made her way into the TV series “Mayberry R.F.D.” she had become a regular fixture of the primetime TV by the late 1960s. She starred in a number of children films. In her teens, she had a breakout and made appearances in The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, Taxi Driver, and Disney’s Freaky Friday, and Candleshoe.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-223 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie1.jpg\" alt=\"jodie1\" width=\"659\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – her Hollywood life continued to flourish. She decided to attend Yale and appeared in the controversial The Accused film. She won the Academy Award and Golden Globe. 3 years later, she took home another Oscar thanks to her role in The Silence of the Lambs as Claire. She still thrives in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-224 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie2.jpg\" alt=\"jodie2\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Howard</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – back in the days, Ron was prominent for his acting. His role in “The Andy Griffith Show” made him so popular in the 60s. His most successful acting role came through the “Happy Days” show as Richie Cunningham, the lead character. He grew up in Milwaukee as a mild-mannered teenager.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Howard is one of the most successful people in the world of television and film in the Hollywood’s history. To say he has succeeded as an actor, producer, or director is not enough. He has been in over 27 files, directed over 28 motion picture films and produced close to 20 other films. He has truly lived to his potential.</h3>\r\n<h3>Kim Richards</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she starred in a number of shows and films through the 70s. She was one the most popular child actors around. She seemed to be all over the public eye with her role in films like Escape to Witch Mountain and its Return from Witch Mountain sequel and shows like “Nanny and the Professor” and “James at Sixteen.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – in 2010, Kim came back into the public and was part of the hit reality series “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills” together with her sister Kyle. There was a rumor of drugs and alcohol abuse soon after starting the show. This was rumored to be partly due to her erratic behavior on camera. Her tribulations went on back in 2015 when she was arrested for public intoxication, trespassing, battery on a police officer and resisting an officer at the Beverly Hills Hotel. She now returns to the show as guest star occasionally.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>The Jacksons</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – remember the “Jackson Five”? The hit group was made of Jackie, Jermaine, Marlon, Michael, and Tito. Their first 4 singles shot to the billboard charts as number one setting a record in the music business back in 1970. The singles were “I Want You Back,” “ABC,” “The Love You Save,” and “I’ll Be There.” The 4 songs were released over 9 months and “I’ll Be There” maintained at the top for 5 weeks.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after 17-year hiatus, the Jacksons reunited to celebrate Michael Jackson’s solo career, back in 2011. They had a Unity Tour where they performed. The brothers still perform even though Michael is dead and Randy retired years ago.</h3>\r\n<h3>Janet</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Janet is the youngest member of the Jackson family. She performed in a number of shows with her older brothers. She was, however, more into acting than singing. She took the role of Penny in the “Good Ties” show as a kid. She played a battered and frightened child, neighbor to the Evans family. She appeared in “Different Strokes” and “Fame” hit shows but still managed her singing career.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Janet has grown to be only second to her brother Michael in the recording industry. She is highly celebrated and sold millions of records. She has starred in hit movies, awarded with multi-platinum albums, and appearing in performances. She is now married to billionaire Wissam Al Mana.</h3>\r\n<h3>Johnny Whitaker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – from “Family Affair” to “General Hospital,” John played in a number of television series. In the Tom Sawyer film, John became the first to give Jodie Foster an on-screen kiss. After the death of his on-screen sister (“Family Affair) Anissa Jones, John had a difficult life and retired from acting for some time.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – John went through a hard life of substance abuse. His family came to his rescue and his 12-step program cleansed him for over a decade now. He can fluently speak Spanish, Portuguese, French and American Sign Language.</h3>\r\n<h3>David Cassidy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, David starred as Keith Partridge. Keith was the lead singer in the family band. He was hired solely for his good looks. In reality, the show producers never cared whether or not he could sing.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he lived on to prove to the producers that he could sing. This went on, and David produced ten albums with The Partridge Family. This saw the plunge of David into superstardom. He has a successful career in music and television.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Mindy Cohn</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Her Natalie portrayal made her so popular. She was an irrepressible “Facts of Life” series’ student back in 1979to 1988. The show’s success is argued to be on Natalie’s character. In some way, this role ‘cursed’ her television role: she could never get a new one.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she earned a Cultural Anthropology degree while still acting. She is a founder of the weSPARK cancer support center. She makes guest television appearances but majorly on voiceover. The “Velma” if the “Scooby-Doo” animation series is her famous voice. She was nominated for Emmy for her work.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mike Lookinland</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Brandy Bunch” show, Mike played the Bobby Brandy role. He was the youngest boy in the family and was usually nice and energetic. His natural hair was sandy brown and curly. His hair had to be dyed and straightened to match the rest in the show.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mike has played in a number of shows like “Little House on The Prairie” and other Brandy Bunch specials and movies such as the Towering Inferno before leaving the show world entirely. He is now married and has two kids with a flourishing concrete business in Utah.</h3>\r\n<h3>Robbie Rist</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the last 6 episodes of “The Brandy Bunch” show, he joined as Cousin Oliver. Rist was actually 9 even though he played as 8-year old Oliver. He came into the show to help in boosting the ratings due to completion from “Sanford &amp; Son” show.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Rist provides voiceover as an adult in various films including the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and other animated shows like the “Batman: The Animated Series.” Film soundtracks for movies like Sharknado and Sharknado 2 are some of his talented works. He also performs as a guitarist, lead singer, drummer and/or bassist of a number Los Angeles rock bands.</h3>\r\n<h3>Robby Benson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known for his film work, Robby was also a star in the TV. He played in show like the “Search for Tomorrow” soap opera and films like Jory, Jeremy, and Ode to Billy Joe, which was a hit. Robby was forced to learn skating so as to play in his famous Ice Castles film.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – thanks to the Disney film Beauty and The Beast, Robby is now known as the voice of the ‘Beast’. He has served as a professor in Utah, New York, South Carolina, and Indiana. He has had around 4 heart surgeries, but he never wanted to discuss the condition with his producers and directors.</h3>\r\n<h3>Helen Hunt</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Helen has never dropped the ball. She is always in movies and TV. Her Oscar-winning performance in the As Good As It Gets is one of her recent films. She had her own hit comedy Ride, back in 2014. During the 911New York attack, she witnessed the ordeal from her apartment. She moved out three days later to Connecticut.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Paolillo</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you have ever watched “Welcome Back Kotter”, then you know Arnold Horshack. He played as a group’s clown in a class of high school kids known as the Sweathogs. He went ahead to perfect his character and learned to love like a hyena.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – in his adult life, Ron was highly demanded. He played a variety of characters for various TV shows and films including “Laverne and Shirley in The Army,” and Friday The Thirteenth among others. He has directed a number of Broadway plays and musicals. He is a fashion designer and wrote a couple of children books. He passed on in 2012 due to a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Susan Dey</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, Susan played Laurie Partridge. She was joined by Shirley Jones and David Cassidy and other actors to make up the cast for the show. Before joining the cast, Dey was a fashion model. Before the show, she had no acting experience.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Dey has been involved in many films including Skyjacked, Disappearance, and Little Women. She has played in various television shows including “L.A.Law.” She refuses the joining of the Partridge Family Reunion and to date, she and Cassidy never speak after their romantic encounter went horrible.</h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Murphy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the popular television series “Bewitched”, made Erin very famous. The series ran from 1964 to 1972. In the early seasons, she played young Tabitha Stephens with Diane, her fraternal twin sister. Erin later took the role herself as the kids grew less alike. She became one of the most famous actresses in the world.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after the end of “Bewitched”, Erin bounced to various auditions, turning down various commercials and modeling jobs. The family later moved to Orange County, and she attended 6th grade here. She married and got her first kid at 21 years. She loved acting, and this led her into teaching the craft. Whenever film shooting was in town, she would work in makeup and production. Her stunt double role for Melissa Leo and Virginia Madsen was great. 10 years later, she went back to Los Angeles and began working on reality TV shows, celebrity judge, and commercials. She owns two companies, and one of them sells frozen vodka martini ice pops. She is married and mother of 6 boys.</h3>\r\n<h3>Karen Carpenter</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Karen plunged into fame as a drummer and singer. Her skill on the instrument was an admiration for many. Luminaries would go on to love her style. Her massive success in the 70s came thanks to her contralto vocal range. Together with Richard, her brother, they had various performances. Her “Close to You” album featured various singles that peaked in the Hot 100.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she passed away European tour where The Carpenters were to perform for Queen Elizabeth. She was involved in performances up until her death.</h3>\r\n<h3>Barry Williams</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the hit series “The Brady Bunch”, Barry played the role of Greg Brady, the eldest child. Her career was flourished and soon after, he became a love for many female fans across the United States. He also recorded 4 albums and together with his TV siblings, the fame came calling.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Barry scooped the Young Artist Foundation Former Child Star Lifetime Achievement Award in 1989. Three years later, the honor was followed by releasing an autobiography, Growing Up Brady…I Was A Teenage Greg. It remained in the list of best-seller for3 months. In 2001, as an executive producer, he turned his book into a made-for-TV movie on NBC. He recently held a guest role in “Brady Bunch” specials and other shows like “That 70’s Show” and “Three’s Company”. Barry spent a good time in the musical theater for roles like in “The Sound of Music,” “West Side Story,” and “Grease.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Maureen McCormick</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Maureen was the leading lady for “The Brady Bunch” show. She is best known for the role played in the show as Marcia Brady between 1969 and 1974.she was Brady’s oldest girl. She portrayed a smart, pretty, and confident girl that was popular in school and home. She was a politics’ enthusiast. Her iconic role came when she was 12 years old.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she married Michael Cummings and got a daughter in 1989, Natalie. After the end of her TV life, she struggled with drug addiction but eventually overcame it. She appeared as a contestant in the “VH1’s Celebrity Fit Club” and won in 2007.</h3>\r\n<h3>Scott Baio</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the former heart-throb teen is popularly known for his role in the “Happy Days” show as Chachi. He was the love interest for Joanie Cunningham (Erin Moran). He played as the leading the musical gangster film called “Bugsy Malone”. The child actors in the film gave it a great twist. Jodie Foster, one of the actors; won the future Academy winner. Baio had beaten over 2,000 kids for this part.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Scott later joined “Joanie Loves Chachi”, a spin-off show after his “Happy Days” time. He later played in other films like Skatetown USA, Zapped, and Foxes among others. He has recently starred in his own reality show. He produces shows for Nick at Nite. He is a registered Republican and was reported to be in an altercation with a barista for failing to name the 2016 Republican presumptive nominee.</h3>\r\n<h3>Danny Bonaduce</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the 70s, Danny rose as a child actor to fame. He played as Danny Partridge in the famous “The Partridge Family.” His bright-red hair and the great ways as a child in the family band bought his name. He was the group’s fictional bass guitar player. In the show, he Danny costarred with David Cassidy. They have remained friends since the first show.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he is now a television and radio personality, professional wrestler, and comedian.  He starred in a number of TV series after the show ended. Some of the series include “Breaking Bonaduce”, a VH1’s reality show back in 205. He hosted radio shows in Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Danny has also been a regular music and talk show host at a Seattle radio known as KZOK-FM as from November 2011.</h3>\r\n<h3>Tatum O’Neal</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – her stats says it all: she won the 1974 Academy Award while at the age of 10. Her turn as Addie Loggins in the Paper Moon made her take home the golden statue. In 1976, she made an appearance in The Bad News Bears and also Nickelodeon the same year. She left a lasting mark in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she got married in 1986 to John McErnroe and got three kids. They divorced in 1994 after separating in 1992. She had a flourishing career in the film industry back in the ‘70s. However, things changed and for the next 15 years, she would only appear in 5 films. Her guest appearance on “8 Simple Rules for Dating My Teenage Daughter” marked her return to the film world in the 2000s. She also appeared in “Law and Order: Criminal Intent” as well as the “Sex and the City.” In 2005, she got a recurring role in the “Rescue Me” hit series. She has gone ahead acting while focusing on her TV shows work.</h3>\r\n<h3>Linda Blair</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she is mostly known for her tricks to vomit pea soup after spinning her head around in circles. Her role in The Exorcist came at 14 years of age. In The Exorcist II: The Heretic, she decided to renew her role as a posse child in 1977. Her Academy Award nomination was thanks to her first role. She won the Golden Globe. She began as a child model at 6 years. Her short-lived daytime soap opera role in the “Hidden Fences” helped to boost her career.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Blair appeared in various horror, and other low-budget exploitation films in the 1980s such films included Hell Night, Savage Streets, and Chained Heat. Later in 1990, her appearance in the Repossessed comedy she made fun of her horror movie roots. In 1996, she made a cameo in the film Scream. She later appeared in the “L.A. 7” BBC TV show and “Grease”. She hosted the “Scariest Places on Earth” by Fox Family between 2000 and 2006. Her guest role in the ”Supernatural” TV show was her recent one.</h3>\r\n<h3>Melissa Gilbert</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Melissa started her career in the late ‘60sand early ‘70s. She did a number of commercials before starring as a guest in various TV roles. During her role as Laura Ingalls Wilder in the “Little House on the Prairie”, she had a big breakthrough. This was between 1974 and 1984. She also appeared in various TV movies such as The Miracle Worker as well as The Diary of Anne Frank.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Melissa has continued acting appearing in various TV programs. “Batman: The Animated Series” is one of her well-known roles wither her voice. From 2001 and 2005, she acted as the President of the Screen Actors Guild. In the “Little House of the Prairie, the Musical”, she played Caroline “Ma” Ingalls. She is loved by her fans and when she contested for hit reality TV show, “Dancing with the Stars”, on NBC it was great for her fans. Some health issues forced her to drop from the Michigan US Congress Democratic race in 2016.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Valerie Bertinelli</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Valerie was born in 1960, and by 1975 she had made a name for herself. She had already started appearing in the “One Day at a Time”, a new sitcom. She appeared in the series’ 208 of the 209 episodes before it came to an end in 1984. In 2005, she reunited with the rest of the show’s cast for the “One Day at a Time Reunion Special.” In 1981, she scooped the Golden Globe at 21 years of age.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Valerie’s career hasn’t shown any signs to slow down. She has been acting all along. She starred in 2 of the ‘90s sitcoms “Café Americain” and “Sydney.” She joined “Touched by an Angel” show that lasted 2 seasons. She later became Jenny Craig’s spokesperson after struggling with her weight for long. She appeared in many commercials for the diet company. She later joined Betty White, Jane Leeves, and Wendie Malick for the TV Land series “Hot in Cleveland” in 2010. The series lasted until June 3 2015.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mackenzie Phillips</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – when she worked on the American Graffiti hit, Mackenzie was only 12. Her stardom continued in the 1970s with her Julie Cooper role in the “One Day at a Time” TV series. By then, she was taking home $50,000 a week. She started doing drugs and drinking by the third season leading to late arrivals on the TV show. She was forced into taking a 6-week break and later entered the Fair Oaks Hospital for treatment. In 1981, she was invited by the producers of the “One Day at a Time” back into the show. She collapsed into the show’s set after getting back into cocaine addiction. She was fired for good.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she checked into rehabilitation for long-term in 1992. She remained here for close to 9 months. Later, she co-starred in the Disney Channel series with Cara DeLizia in 1999. It was called “So Weird” playing a fictional rock star Molly Phillips. During her time in the “ER,” “Without a Trace,” “Cold Case,” and “7th Heaven”, she was a guest star. She later became a rehab counselor to help others at the Breathe Life Healing Center in West Hollywood, California.</h3>\r\n<h3>Kristy McNichol</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – McNichol began her young career in commercials and then into guest appearances in some series like “Starsky &amp; Hutch,” “Love American Style” and “The Bionic Woman” as well as “The Love Boat.” Her Patricia Apple role in the “Apple’s Way” series was her first regular series job. The 1976 “Family” drama series saw her earn the Emmy Awards for Best Supporting Actress in a Dramatic Series. Later, she went into music and recorded the Kristy &amp; Jimmy McNichol album for RCA Records. “He’s So Fine” hit was her best and it peaked at #70.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – her role in the Little Darlings movie continued to make a name for her. She co-starred with Matt Dillon, Cynthia Dixon, and Tatum O’Neal. Alongside Dennis Quaid and Mark Hamill, she appeared in The Night the Lights Went Out in Georgia. A year later, Kristy would appear in Only When I Laugh by Neil Simon. She was then nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress. Before leaving the cast of “Empty Nest”, Kristy appeared in several seasons but returned for the final episode in 1995. She has left the screen since then but continues to voice characters in various animated series like “Invasion America” and “Extreme Ghostbusters.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Adam Rich</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Rich is best known for the television series “Eight Is Enough.” He played as Nicholas Bradford, the youngest son. It ran from 1977 to 81 for five seasons. His bowl haircut was an inspiration to many parents who did the same for their kids.it was one of his recognizable aspects. He was known as “America’s little brother” for this iconic role. He had a rough encounter in the ‘80s, and he went under for good.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at 14, Rich had started smoking Marijuana. Things went even worse at 17 when he dropped out of high school. He almost lost his life to Valium overdose in 1989. His pharmacy burglar attempt in 1991 got him arrested. 5 years later, Might – a San Francisco-based magazine – published a death hoax through his consent claiming to have been murdered. In 2001, he was arrested for driving under the influence. He has entered and left the rehab for at least 3 times. Currently, he is shopping around for new TV films and shows’ script ideas.</h3>\r\n<h3>Tanya Tucker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at just 13 years of age, this kid shot into the country charts thanks to her “Delta Dawn” hit. Mel Tillis was the first one to discover her. This was through a stage invitation thanks to her vocal skills. In 1969, her family moved to Las Vegas and not long before she was regularly performing in the city. She gained Dolores Fuller’s attention and later signed to Colombia Records.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Tanya had a successful career. Decades after her first hit, she became one of the most successful country singers of all time. She collected a streak of Top 10 and Top 40 hits. Her country music prowess saw her get nominated for various Country Music Association awards. She released various albums that were popular.  Some of her hits included “Blood Red and Goin’ Down” and “What’s Your Mama’s Name?” of 1973. 2 years later, another hit came by: “Lizzie and Rainman.” It was later followed by the “Strong Enough to Bend” in 1988. She is arguably one of the few childhood stars to carry their fans into adulthood stardom. She has been reckoned as a top influence in the female country music world.</h3>\r\n<h3>Danielle Spencer</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Danielle played the part of Dee Thomas in the “What’s Happening” television show. In the cast, she played as the “more than annoying little sister” and did so with aplomb. She is famously known for her favorite saying: “Ooooohh, I’m tellin’ Mama!” The show lasted from August 1976 to April 1979.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Spencer is now a doctor of b=veterinary medicine in California. In 2014, she was diagnosed with breast cancer but she was lucky to beat it. She is the only kid actor to be inducted into the Smithsonian Museum as a permanent exhibition on African American Culture.</h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Moran</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the television show “Happy Days”, Erin played the youngest child of the Cunningham family. She played Joanie Cunningham with a sense of timing and comedy skills that were considered perfect for a “brat sister.” She played this part from 1974 to 1984 and later from 1982 to 1983 during the spin-off “Joanie Loves Chachi.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after “Happy Days”, she played sporadic roles. She would later get into financial issues. Things went south when Moran’s downward took to a spiral and the world watched her drink in public. She was evicted from their house and forced to move into a trailer with her mother-in-law and husband.</h3>\r\n<h3>Lance Kerwin</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you are familiar with Salem’s Lot, “The Family Holvak,” and “James at Fifteen (and Sixteen),” then you know who Lance Kerwin. He played all of them with other 20 more roles in television and film in the 70s. As a child star, Kerwin played in his show of the decade “Emergency” and in 1979, he played his last: Salem’s Lot.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Kerwin retired in 1995 after a successful acting career. He worked as a minister in Kaua’i, Hawaii. He still lies there. Lance had admitted to having smoked pot before his 10th birthday. He was a crack user at his 20s. He had to go through a number of rehab stints. He got clean, and his wife pledged guilty to fraud. It was later discovered that he had falsified papers to get food stamps. He had around 3 homes in the USA.</h3>\r\n<h3>Leif Garrett</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – like David Cassidy, Leif was a brilliant child actor, TV personality, and singer.Leif started the ‘70s with a bang: the film Walking Tall was the opener and drew the curtains with Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. He made appearances in at least 10 films and TV shows. He impressed everyone he worked with. In the late 70s, his personal difficulties.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – it is true to say that Leif’s downfall was crafted by his partying, drugs and celebrity life. At 17, he crashed a leased Porsche 1979, leaving his friend a paraplegic. He has been in and out of drug and legal troubles. He has been arrested for heroin possession and once bought cocaine from undercover cops. His adult life has been marred by controversy and drama. He was ordered for rehab.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mason Reese</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his look and talent were Mason’s perfect recipe for his stardom in the 70s. He acted in 70 TV commercials alone. He was ever on shows such as “Mike Douglas” and “Howard Cosell.” He was literally on almost every talk show back then. He lived as a pop star back in the days.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mason became a restaurateur after his TV retirement. He opened a number of restaurants like Paladar and Destination Bar and Grille in the area of Manhattan. He has been raising money to make the pending “Life Interrupted” TV pilot. The show featured Dan Wells, who played in “Gilligan’s Island” as Mary Ann; Alison Arngrim, who played Neil Oleson in ”Little House on the Prairie;” Erin Murphy, who played Tabitha on “Bewitched;” and Michael Learned, who played Olivia Walton in “The Waltons;” as well as “The Brady Bunch’s” Robbie Rich, who played Cousin Oliver among other television icons.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mark Lester</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known by US fans thanks to his Oliver Twist’s character, Lester made his film debut at 6 years. During the musical adaption of the film, he took the role of Oliver at 8 years. He could never sing, so all his singing was dubbed by musical director’s daughter in the Oliver Twist.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at the age of 19 Lester retired from acting and went to school. He went to be an osteopath. He was a close friend of Michael Jackson, and they became Godfathers to each other’s children. There claims that he gave sperm to Michael Jackson to conceive and the chances are that the children are his biologically.</h3>\r\n<h3>Haywood Nelson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his Dwayne Nelson role in the “What’s Happening!!” series made him so popular. The series aired between 1976 and 1979. He starred in the spin-off series “What’s Happening Now!!” from1985 to 1988. As a child, Nelson appeared in various national commercials and later in the movie Mixed Company. In 1974, alongside Mario Thomas, Nelson appeared on Broadway in Thieves. He starred in “Sanford and Son” at 14 years as Grady’s grandson. He later starred in the “Grady”, a spin-off of “Sanford and Son.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Nelson had difficulties landing another TV show of such a national appeal. However, he has continued to work in TV. He guest-starred in the “Kojak” before he went to work behind the scenes. He has been recently working with talk shows’ crew, TV shows, and interview programs. He is among the first African American teen idols to be nationally recognized.</h3>','Top Child Stars of the 70s - Now and Then','','inherit','closed','closed','','199-revision-v1','','','2016-12-01 14:17:07','2016-12-01 14:17:07','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/2016/12/01/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(272,2,'2016-12-01 14:32:43','2016-12-01 14:32:43','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Jodie Foster</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at 3 years, Jodie had begun her acting career. At 5 years, she made her way into the TV series “Mayberry R.F.D.” she had become a regular fixture of the primetime TV by the late 1960s. She starred in a number of children films. In her teens, she had a breakout and made appearances in The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, Taxi Driver, and Disney’s Freaky Friday, and Candleshoe.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-223 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie1.jpg\" alt=\"jodie1\" width=\"659\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – her Hollywood life continued to flourish. She decided to attend Yale and appeared in the controversial The Accused film. She won the Academy Award and Golden Globe. 3 years later, she took home another Oscar thanks to her role in The Silence of the Lambs as Claire. She still thrives in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-224 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie2.jpg\" alt=\"jodie2\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n<h3> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Howard</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – back in the days, Ron was prominent for his acting. His role in “The Andy Griffith Show” made him so popular in the 60s. His most successful acting role came through the “Happy Days” show as Richie Cunningham, the lead character. He grew up in Milwaukee as a mild-mannered teenager.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-257 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron1.jpg\" alt=\"ron1\" width=\"592\" height=\"296\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Howard is one of the most successful people in the world of television and film in the Hollywood’s history. To say he has succeeded as an actor, producer, or director is not enough. He has been in over 27 files, directed over 28 motion picture films and produced close to 20 other films. He has truly lived to his potential.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-258\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron2.jpg\" alt=\"ron2\" width=\"656\" height=\"328\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Kim Richards</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she starred in a number of shows and films through the 70s. She was one the most popular child actors around. She seemed to be all over the public eye with her role in films like Escape to Witch Mountain and its Return from Witch Mountain sequel and shows like “Nanny and the Professor” and “James at Sixteen.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-229 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim1.jpg\" alt=\"kim1\" width=\"597\" height=\"336\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – in 2010, Kim came back into the public and was part of the hit reality series “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills” together with her sister Kyle. There was a rumor of drugs and alcohol abuse soon after starting the show. This was rumored to be partly due to her erratic behavior on camera. Her tribulations went on back in 2015 when she was arrested for public intoxication, trespassing, battery on a police officer and resisting an officer at the Beverly Hills Hotel. She now returns to the show as guest star occasionally.</h3>\r\n<h3> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-230 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim2.jpg\" alt=\"kim2\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>The Jacksons</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – remember the “Jackson Five”? The hit group was made of Jackie, Jermaine, Marlon, Michael, and Tito. Their first 4 singles shot to the billboard charts as number one setting a record in the music business back in 1970. The singles were “I Want You Back,” “ABC,” “The Love You Save,” and “I’ll Be There.” The 4 songs were released over 9 months and “I’ll Be There” maintained at the top for 5 weeks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-219 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson1.jpg\" alt=\"jackson1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – after 17-year hiatus, the Jacksons reunited to celebrate Michael Jackson’s solo career, back in 2011. They had a Unity Tour where they performed. The brothers still perform even though Michael is dead and Randy retired years ago.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-220 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson2.jpg\" alt=\"jackson2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage-->Janet</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Janet is the youngest member of the Jackson family. She performed in a number of shows with her older brothers. She was, however, more into acting than singing. She took the role of Penny in the “Good Ties” show as a kid. She played a battered and frightened child, neighbor to the Evans family. She appeared in “Different Strokes” and “Fame” hit shows but still managed her singing career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-221\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet1.jpg\" alt=\"LOS ANGELES - JANUARY 1: Actresses Janet Jackson (left) and Ja\'net Dubois appear in a scene from the CBS television comedy series &quot;GOOD TIMES&quot; in 1974 in Los Angeles, CA. (Photo by CBS via Getty Images)\" width=\"600\" height=\"439\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Janet has grown to be only second to her brother Michael in the recording industry. She is highly celebrated and sold millions of records. She has starred in hit movies, awarded with multi-platinum albums, and appearing in performances. She is now married to billionaire Wissam Al Mana.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-222\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet2.jpg\" alt=\"162420084SR00004_Sergio_Ros\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Johnny Whitaker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – from “Family Affair” to “General Hospital,” John played in a number of television series. In the Tom Sawyer film, John became the first to give Jodie Foster an on-screen kiss. After the death of his on-screen sister (“Family Affair) Anissa Jones, John had a difficult life and retired from acting for some time.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – John went through a hard life of substance abuse. His family came to his rescue and his 12-step program cleansed him for over a decade now. He can fluently speak Spanish, Portuguese, French and American Sign Language.</h3>\r\n<h3>David Cassidy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, David starred as Keith Partridge. Keith was the lead singer in the family band. He was hired solely for his good looks. In reality, the show producers never cared whether or not he could sing.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he lived on to prove to the producers that he could sing. This went on, and David produced ten albums with The Partridge Family. This saw the plunge of David into superstardom. He has a successful career in music and television.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Mindy Cohn</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Her Natalie portrayal made her so popular. She was an irrepressible “Facts of Life” series’ student back in 1979to 1988. The show’s success is argued to be on Natalie’s character. In some way, this role ‘cursed’ her television role: she could never get a new one.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she earned a Cultural Anthropology degree while still acting. She is a founder of the weSPARK cancer support center. She makes guest television appearances but majorly on voiceover. The “Velma” if the “Scooby-Doo” animation series is her famous voice. She was nominated for Emmy for her work.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mike Lookinland</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Brandy Bunch” show, Mike played the Bobby Brandy role. He was the youngest boy in the family and was usually nice and energetic. His natural hair was sandy brown and curly. His hair had to be dyed and straightened to match the rest in the show.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mike has played in a number of shows like “Little House on The Prairie” and other Brandy Bunch specials and movies such as the Towering Inferno before leaving the show world entirely. He is now married and has two kids with a flourishing concrete business in Utah.</h3>\r\n<h3>Robbie Rist</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the last 6 episodes of “The Brandy Bunch” show, he joined as Cousin Oliver. Rist was actually 9 even though he played as 8-year old Oliver. He came into the show to help in boosting the ratings due to completion from “Sanford &amp; Son” show.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Rist provides voiceover as an adult in various films including the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and other animated shows like the “Batman: The Animated Series.” Film soundtracks for movies like Sharknado and Sharknado 2 are some of his talented works. He also performs as a guitarist, lead singer, drummer and/or bassist of a number Los Angeles rock bands.</h3>\r\n<h3>Robby Benson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known for his film work, Robby was also a star in the TV. He played in show like the “Search for Tomorrow” soap opera and films like Jory, Jeremy, and Ode to Billy Joe, which was a hit. Robby was forced to learn skating so as to play in his famous Ice Castles film.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – thanks to the Disney film Beauty and The Beast, Robby is now known as the voice of the ‘Beast’. He has served as a professor in Utah, New York, South Carolina, and Indiana. He has had around 4 heart surgeries, but he never wanted to discuss the condition with his producers and directors.</h3>\r\n<h3>Helen Hunt</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Helen has never dropped the ball. She is always in movies and TV. Her Oscar-winning performance in the As Good As It Gets is one of her recent films. She had her own hit comedy Ride, back in 2014. During the 911New York attack, she witnessed the ordeal from her apartment. She moved out three days later to Connecticut.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Paolillo</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you have ever watched “Welcome Back Kotter”, then you know Arnold Horshack. He played as a group’s clown in a class of high school kids known as the Sweathogs. He went ahead to perfect his character and learned to love like a hyena.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – in his adult life, Ron was highly demanded. He played a variety of characters for various TV shows and films including “Laverne and Shirley in The Army,” and Friday The Thirteenth among others. He has directed a number of Broadway plays and musicals. He is a fashion designer and wrote a couple of children books. He passed on in 2012 due to a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Susan Dey</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, Susan played Laurie Partridge. She was joined by Shirley Jones and David Cassidy and other actors to make up the cast for the show. Before joining the cast, Dey was a fashion model. Before the show, she had no acting experience.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Dey has been involved in many films including Skyjacked, Disappearance, and Little Women. She has played in various television shows including “L.A.Law.” She refuses the joining of the Partridge Family Reunion and to date, she and Cassidy never speak after their romantic encounter went horrible.</h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Murphy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the popular television series “Bewitched”, made Erin very famous. The series ran from 1964 to 1972. In the early seasons, she played young Tabitha Stephens with Diane, her fraternal twin sister. Erin later took the role herself as the kids grew less alike. She became one of the most famous actresses in the world.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after the end of “Bewitched”, Erin bounced to various auditions, turning down various commercials and modeling jobs. The family later moved to Orange County, and she attended 6th grade here. She married and got her first kid at 21 years. She loved acting, and this led her into teaching the craft. Whenever film shooting was in town, she would work in makeup and production. Her stunt double role for Melissa Leo and Virginia Madsen was great. 10 years later, she went back to Los Angeles and began working on reality TV shows, celebrity judge, and commercials. She owns two companies, and one of them sells frozen vodka martini ice pops. She is married and mother of 6 boys.</h3>\r\n<h3>Karen Carpenter</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Karen plunged into fame as a drummer and singer. Her skill on the instrument was an admiration for many. Luminaries would go on to love her style. Her massive success in the 70s came thanks to her contralto vocal range. Together with Richard, her brother, they had various performances. Her “Close to You” album featured various singles that peaked in the Hot 100.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she passed away European tour where The Carpenters were to perform for Queen Elizabeth. She was involved in performances up until her death.</h3>\r\n<h3>Barry Williams</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the hit series “The Brady Bunch”, Barry played the role of Greg Brady, the eldest child. Her career was flourished and soon after, he became a love for many female fans across the United States. He also recorded 4 albums and together with his TV siblings, the fame came calling.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Barry scooped the Young Artist Foundation Former Child Star Lifetime Achievement Award in 1989. Three years later, the honor was followed by releasing an autobiography, Growing Up Brady…I Was A Teenage Greg. It remained in the list of best-seller for3 months. In 2001, as an executive producer, he turned his book into a made-for-TV movie on NBC. He recently held a guest role in “Brady Bunch” specials and other shows like “That 70’s Show” and “Three’s Company”. Barry spent a good time in the musical theater for roles like in “The Sound of Music,” “West Side Story,” and “Grease.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Maureen McCormick</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Maureen was the leading lady for “The Brady Bunch” show. She is best known for the role played in the show as Marcia Brady between 1969 and 1974.she was Brady’s oldest girl. She portrayed a smart, pretty, and confident girl that was popular in school and home. She was a politics’ enthusiast. Her iconic role came when she was 12 years old.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she married Michael Cummings and got a daughter in 1989, Natalie. After the end of her TV life, she struggled with drug addiction but eventually overcame it. She appeared as a contestant in the “VH1’s Celebrity Fit Club” and won in 2007.</h3>\r\n<h3>Scott Baio</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the former heart-throb teen is popularly known for his role in the “Happy Days” show as Chachi. He was the love interest for Joanie Cunningham (Erin Moran). He played as the leading the musical gangster film called “Bugsy Malone”. The child actors in the film gave it a great twist. Jodie Foster, one of the actors; won the future Academy winner. Baio had beaten over 2,000 kids for this part.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Scott later joined “Joanie Loves Chachi”, a spin-off show after his “Happy Days” time. He later played in other films like Skatetown USA, Zapped, and Foxes among others. He has recently starred in his own reality show. He produces shows for Nick at Nite. He is a registered Republican and was reported to be in an altercation with a barista for failing to name the 2016 Republican presumptive nominee.</h3>\r\n<h3>Danny Bonaduce</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the 70s, Danny rose as a child actor to fame. He played as Danny Partridge in the famous “The Partridge Family.” His bright-red hair and the great ways as a child in the family band bought his name. He was the group’s fictional bass guitar player. In the show, he Danny costarred with David Cassidy. They have remained friends since the first show.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he is now a television and radio personality, professional wrestler, and comedian.  He starred in a number of TV series after the show ended. Some of the series include “Breaking Bonaduce”, a VH1’s reality show back in 205. He hosted radio shows in Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Danny has also been a regular music and talk show host at a Seattle radio known as KZOK-FM as from November 2011.</h3>\r\n<h3>Tatum O’Neal</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – her stats says it all: she won the 1974 Academy Award while at the age of 10. Her turn as Addie Loggins in the Paper Moon made her take home the golden statue. In 1976, she made an appearance in The Bad News Bears and also Nickelodeon the same year. She left a lasting mark in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she got married in 1986 to John McErnroe and got three kids. They divorced in 1994 after separating in 1992. She had a flourishing career in the film industry back in the ‘70s. However, things changed and for the next 15 years, she would only appear in 5 films. Her guest appearance on “8 Simple Rules for Dating My Teenage Daughter” marked her return to the film world in the 2000s. She also appeared in “Law and Order: Criminal Intent” as well as the “Sex and the City.” In 2005, she got a recurring role in the “Rescue Me” hit series. She has gone ahead acting while focusing on her TV shows work.</h3>\r\n<h3>Linda Blair</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she is mostly known for her tricks to vomit pea soup after spinning her head around in circles. Her role in The Exorcist came at 14 years of age. In The Exorcist II: The Heretic, she decided to renew her role as a posse child in 1977. Her Academy Award nomination was thanks to her first role. She won the Golden Globe. She began as a child model at 6 years. Her short-lived daytime soap opera role in the “Hidden Fences” helped to boost her career.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Blair appeared in various horror, and other low-budget exploitation films in the 1980s such films included Hell Night, Savage Streets, and Chained Heat. Later in 1990, her appearance in the Repossessed comedy she made fun of her horror movie roots. In 1996, she made a cameo in the film Scream. She later appeared in the “L.A. 7” BBC TV show and “Grease”. She hosted the “Scariest Places on Earth” by Fox Family between 2000 and 2006. Her guest role in the ”Supernatural” TV show was her recent one.</h3>\r\n<h3>Melissa Gilbert</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Melissa started her career in the late ‘60sand early ‘70s. She did a number of commercials before starring as a guest in various TV roles. During her role as Laura Ingalls Wilder in the “Little House on the Prairie”, she had a big breakthrough. This was between 1974 and 1984. She also appeared in various TV movies such as The Miracle Worker as well as The Diary of Anne Frank.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Melissa has continued acting appearing in various TV programs. “Batman: The Animated Series” is one of her well-known roles wither her voice. From 2001 and 2005, she acted as the President of the Screen Actors Guild. In the “Little House of the Prairie, the Musical”, she played Caroline “Ma” Ingalls. She is loved by her fans and when she contested for hit reality TV show, “Dancing with the Stars”, on NBC it was great for her fans. Some health issues forced her to drop from the Michigan US Congress Democratic race in 2016.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Valerie Bertinelli</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Valerie was born in 1960, and by 1975 she had made a name for herself. She had already started appearing in the “One Day at a Time”, a new sitcom. She appeared in the series’ 208 of the 209 episodes before it came to an end in 1984. In 2005, she reunited with the rest of the show’s cast for the “One Day at a Time Reunion Special.” In 1981, she scooped the Golden Globe at 21 years of age.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Valerie’s career hasn’t shown any signs to slow down. She has been acting all along. She starred in 2 of the ‘90s sitcoms “Café Americain” and “Sydney.” She joined “Touched by an Angel” show that lasted 2 seasons. She later became Jenny Craig’s spokesperson after struggling with her weight for long. She appeared in many commercials for the diet company. She later joined Betty White, Jane Leeves, and Wendie Malick for the TV Land series “Hot in Cleveland” in 2010. The series lasted until June 3 2015.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mackenzie Phillips</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – when she worked on the American Graffiti hit, Mackenzie was only 12. Her stardom continued in the 1970s with her Julie Cooper role in the “One Day at a Time” TV series. By then, she was taking home $50,000 a week. She started doing drugs and drinking by the third season leading to late arrivals on the TV show. She was forced into taking a 6-week break and later entered the Fair Oaks Hospital for treatment. In 1981, she was invited by the producers of the “One Day at a Time” back into the show. She collapsed into the show’s set after getting back into cocaine addiction. She was fired for good.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she checked into rehabilitation for long-term in 1992. She remained here for close to 9 months. Later, she co-starred in the Disney Channel series with Cara DeLizia in 1999. It was called “So Weird” playing a fictional rock star Molly Phillips. During her time in the “ER,” “Without a Trace,” “Cold Case,” and “7th Heaven”, she was a guest star. She later became a rehab counselor to help others at the Breathe Life Healing Center in West Hollywood, California.</h3>\r\n<h3>Kristy McNichol</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – McNichol began her young career in commercials and then into guest appearances in some series like “Starsky &amp; Hutch,” “Love American Style” and “The Bionic Woman” as well as “The Love Boat.” Her Patricia Apple role in the “Apple’s Way” series was her first regular series job. The 1976 “Family” drama series saw her earn the Emmy Awards for Best Supporting Actress in a Dramatic Series. Later, she went into music and recorded the Kristy &amp; Jimmy McNichol album for RCA Records. “He’s So Fine” hit was her best and it peaked at #70.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – her role in the Little Darlings movie continued to make a name for her. She co-starred with Matt Dillon, Cynthia Dixon, and Tatum O’Neal. Alongside Dennis Quaid and Mark Hamill, she appeared in The Night the Lights Went Out in Georgia. A year later, Kristy would appear in Only When I Laugh by Neil Simon. She was then nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress. Before leaving the cast of “Empty Nest”, Kristy appeared in several seasons but returned for the final episode in 1995. She has left the screen since then but continues to voice characters in various animated series like “Invasion America” and “Extreme Ghostbusters.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Adam Rich</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Rich is best known for the television series “Eight Is Enough.” He played as Nicholas Bradford, the youngest son. It ran from 1977 to 81 for five seasons. His bowl haircut was an inspiration to many parents who did the same for their kids.it was one of his recognizable aspects. He was known as “America’s little brother” for this iconic role. He had a rough encounter in the ‘80s, and he went under for good.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at 14, Rich had started smoking Marijuana. Things went even worse at 17 when he dropped out of high school. He almost lost his life to Valium overdose in 1989. His pharmacy burglar attempt in 1991 got him arrested. 5 years later, Might – a San Francisco-based magazine – published a death hoax through his consent claiming to have been murdered. In 2001, he was arrested for driving under the influence. He has entered and left the rehab for at least 3 times. Currently, he is shopping around for new TV films and shows’ script ideas.</h3>\r\n<h3>Tanya Tucker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at just 13 years of age, this kid shot into the country charts thanks to her “Delta Dawn” hit. Mel Tillis was the first one to discover her. This was through a stage invitation thanks to her vocal skills. In 1969, her family moved to Las Vegas and not long before she was regularly performing in the city. She gained Dolores Fuller’s attention and later signed to Colombia Records.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Tanya had a successful career. Decades after her first hit, she became one of the most successful country singers of all time. She collected a streak of Top 10 and Top 40 hits. Her country music prowess saw her get nominated for various Country Music Association awards. She released various albums that were popular.  Some of her hits included “Blood Red and Goin’ Down” and “What’s Your Mama’s Name?” of 1973. 2 years later, another hit came by: “Lizzie and Rainman.” It was later followed by the “Strong Enough to Bend” in 1988. She is arguably one of the few childhood stars to carry their fans into adulthood stardom. She has been reckoned as a top influence in the female country music world.</h3>\r\n<h3>Danielle Spencer</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Danielle played the part of Dee Thomas in the “What’s Happening” television show. In the cast, she played as the “more than annoying little sister” and did so with aplomb. She is famously known for her favorite saying: “Ooooohh, I’m tellin’ Mama!” The show lasted from August 1976 to April 1979.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Spencer is now a doctor of b=veterinary medicine in California. In 2014, she was diagnosed with breast cancer but she was lucky to beat it. She is the only kid actor to be inducted into the Smithsonian Museum as a permanent exhibition on African American Culture.</h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Moran</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the television show “Happy Days”, Erin played the youngest child of the Cunningham family. She played Joanie Cunningham with a sense of timing and comedy skills that were considered perfect for a “brat sister.” She played this part from 1974 to 1984 and later from 1982 to 1983 during the spin-off “Joanie Loves Chachi.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after “Happy Days”, she played sporadic roles. She would later get into financial issues. Things went south when Moran’s downward took to a spiral and the world watched her drink in public. She was evicted from their house and forced to move into a trailer with her mother-in-law and husband.</h3>\r\n<h3>Lance Kerwin</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you are familiar with Salem’s Lot, “The Family Holvak,” and “James at Fifteen (and Sixteen),” then you know who Lance Kerwin. He played all of them with other 20 more roles in television and film in the 70s. As a child star, Kerwin played in his show of the decade “Emergency” and in 1979, he played his last: Salem’s Lot.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Kerwin retired in 1995 after a successful acting career. He worked as a minister in Kaua’i, Hawaii. He still lies there. Lance had admitted to having smoked pot before his 10th birthday. He was a crack user at his 20s. He had to go through a number of rehab stints. He got clean, and his wife pledged guilty to fraud. It was later discovered that he had falsified papers to get food stamps. He had around 3 homes in the USA.</h3>\r\n<h3>Leif Garrett</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – like David Cassidy, Leif was a brilliant child actor, TV personality, and singer.Leif started the ‘70s with a bang: the film Walking Tall was the opener and drew the curtains with Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. He made appearances in at least 10 films and TV shows. He impressed everyone he worked with. In the late 70s, his personal difficulties.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – it is true to say that Leif’s downfall was crafted by his partying, drugs and celebrity life. At 17, he crashed a leased Porsche 1979, leaving his friend a paraplegic. He has been in and out of drug and legal troubles. He has been arrested for heroin possession and once bought cocaine from undercover cops. His adult life has been marred by controversy and drama. He was ordered for rehab.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mason Reese</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his look and talent were Mason’s perfect recipe for his stardom in the 70s. He acted in 70 TV commercials alone. He was ever on shows such as “Mike Douglas” and “Howard Cosell.” He was literally on almost every talk show back then. He lived as a pop star back in the days.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mason became a restaurateur after his TV retirement. He opened a number of restaurants like Paladar and Destination Bar and Grille in the area of Manhattan. He has been raising money to make the pending “Life Interrupted” TV pilot. The show featured Dan Wells, who played in “Gilligan’s Island” as Mary Ann; Alison Arngrim, who played Neil Oleson in ”Little House on the Prairie;” Erin Murphy, who played Tabitha on “Bewitched;” and Michael Learned, who played Olivia Walton in “The Waltons;” as well as “The Brady Bunch’s” Robbie Rich, who played Cousin Oliver among other television icons.</h3>\r\n<h3>Mark Lester</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known by US fans thanks to his Oliver Twist’s character, Lester made his film debut at 6 years. During the musical adaption of the film, he took the role of Oliver at 8 years. He could never sing, so all his singing was dubbed by musical director’s daughter in the Oliver Twist.</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at the age of 19 Lester retired from acting and went to school. He went to be an osteopath. He was a close friend of Michael Jackson, and they became Godfathers to each other’s children. There claims that he gave sperm to Michael Jackson to conceive and the chances are that the children are his biologically.</h3>\r\n<h3>Haywood Nelson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his Dwayne Nelson role in the “What’s Happening!!” series made him so popular. The series aired between 1976 and 1979. He starred in the spin-off series “What’s Happening Now!!” from1985 to 1988. As a child, Nelson appeared in various national commercials and later in the movie Mixed Company. In 1974, alongside Mario Thomas, Nelson appeared on Broadway in Thieves. He starred in “Sanford and Son” at 14 years as Grady’s grandson. He later starred in the “Grady”, a spin-off of “Sanford and Son.”</h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Nelson had difficulties landing another TV show of such a national appeal. However, he has continued to work in TV. He guest-starred in the “Kojak” before he went to work behind the scenes. He has been recently working with talk shows’ crew, TV shows, and interview programs. He is among the first African American teen idols to be nationally recognized.</h3>','Top Child Stars of the 70s - Now and Then','','inherit','closed','closed','','199-revision-v1','','','2016-12-01 14:32:43','2016-12-01 14:32:43','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/2016/12/01/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(273,2,'2016-12-01 15:01:29','2016-12-01 15:01:29','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Jodie Foster</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at 3 years, Jodie had begun her acting career. At 5 years, she made her way into the TV series “Mayberry R.F.D.” she had become a regular fixture of the primetime TV by the late 1960s. She starred in a number of children films. In her teens, she had a breakout and made appearances in The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, Taxi Driver, and Disney’s Freaky Friday, and Candleshoe.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-223 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie1.jpg\" alt=\"jodie1\" width=\"659\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – her Hollywood life continued to flourish. She decided to attend Yale and appeared in the controversial The Accused film. She won the Academy Award and Golden Globe. 3 years later, she took home another Oscar thanks to her role in The Silence of the Lambs as Claire. She still thrives in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-224 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie2.jpg\" alt=\"jodie2\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n<h3> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Howard</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – back in the days, Ron was prominent for his acting. His role in “The Andy Griffith Show” made him so popular in the 60s. His most successful acting role came through the “Happy Days” show as Richie Cunningham, the lead character. He grew up in Milwaukee as a mild-mannered teenager.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-257 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron1.jpg\" alt=\"ron1\" width=\"592\" height=\"296\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Howard is one of the most successful people in the world of television and film in the Hollywood’s history. To say he has succeeded as an actor, producer, or director is not enough. He has been in over 27 files, directed over 28 motion picture films and produced close to 20 other films. He has truly lived to his potential.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-258\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron2.jpg\" alt=\"ron2\" width=\"656\" height=\"328\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Kim Richards</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she starred in a number of shows and films through the 70s. She was one the most popular child actors around. She seemed to be all over the public eye with her role in films like Escape to Witch Mountain and its Return from Witch Mountain sequel and shows like “Nanny and the Professor” and “James at Sixteen.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-229 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim1.jpg\" alt=\"kim1\" width=\"597\" height=\"336\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – in 2010, Kim came back into the public and was part of the hit reality series “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills” together with her sister Kyle. There was a rumor of drugs and alcohol abuse soon after starting the show. This was rumored to be partly due to her erratic behavior on camera. Her tribulations went on back in 2015 when she was arrested for public intoxication, trespassing, battery on a police officer and resisting an officer at the Beverly Hills Hotel. She now returns to the show as guest star occasionally.</h3>\r\n<h3> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-230 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim2.jpg\" alt=\"kim2\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>The Jacksons</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – remember the “Jackson Five”? The hit group was made of Jackie, Jermaine, Marlon, Michael, and Tito. Their first 4 singles shot to the billboard charts as number one setting a record in the music business back in 1970. The singles were “I Want You Back,” “ABC,” “The Love You Save,” and “I’ll Be There.” The 4 songs were released over 9 months and “I’ll Be There” maintained at the top for 5 weeks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-219 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson1.jpg\" alt=\"jackson1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – after 17-year hiatus, the Jacksons reunited to celebrate Michael Jackson’s solo career, back in 2011. They had a Unity Tour where they performed. The brothers still perform even though Michael is dead and Randy retired years ago.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-220 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson2.jpg\" alt=\"jackson2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage-->Janet</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Janet is the youngest member of the Jackson family. She performed in a number of shows with her older brothers. She was, however, more into acting than singing. She took the role of Penny in the “Good Ties” show as a kid. She played a battered and frightened child, neighbor to the Evans family. She appeared in “Different Strokes” and “Fame” hit shows but still managed her singing career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-221\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet1.jpg\" alt=\"LOS ANGELES - JANUARY 1: Actresses Janet Jackson (left) and Ja\'net Dubois appear in a scene from the CBS television comedy series &quot;GOOD TIMES&quot; in 1974 in Los Angeles, CA. (Photo by CBS via Getty Images)\" width=\"600\" height=\"439\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Janet has grown to be only second to her brother Michael in the recording industry. She is highly celebrated and sold millions of records. She has starred in hit movies, awarded with multi-platinum albums, and appearing in performances. She is now married to billionaire Wissam Al Mana.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-222\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet2.jpg\" alt=\"162420084SR00004_Sergio_Ros\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Johnny Whitaker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – from “Family Affair” to “General Hospital,” John played in a number of television series. In the Tom Sawyer film, John became the first to give Jodie Foster an on-screen kiss. After the death of his on-screen sister (“Family Affair) Anissa Jones, John had a difficult life and retired from acting for some time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-225\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/johny1.jpg\" alt=\"johny1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – John went through a hard life of substance abuse. His family came to his rescue and his 12-step program cleansed him for over a decade now. He can fluently speak Spanish, Portuguese, French and American Sign Language.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-226\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/johny2.jpg\" alt=\"johny2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>David Cassidy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, David starred as Keith Partridge. Keith was the lead singer in the family band. He was hired solely for his good looks. In reality, the show producers never cared whether or not he could sing.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-209\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/David-cassidy-then.jpg\" alt=\"david-cassidy-then\" width=\"600\" height=\"303\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he lived on to prove to the producers that he could sing. This went on, and David produced ten albums with The Partridge Family. This saw the plunge of David into superstardom. He has a successful career in music and television.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-204\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/cassidy1.jpg\" alt=\"cassidy1\" width=\"594\" height=\"297\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mindy Cohn</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Her Natalie portrayal made her so popular. She was an irrepressible “Facts of Life” series’ student back in 1979to 1988. The show’s success is argued to be on Natalie’s character. In some way, this role ‘cursed’ her television role: she could never get a new one.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-251\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mindy1.jpg\" alt=\"mindy1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she earned a Cultural Anthropology degree while still acting. She is a founder of the weSPARK cancer support center. She makes guest television appearances but majorly on voiceover. The “Velma” if the “Scooby-Doo” animation series is her famous voice. She was nominated for Emmy for her work.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-252\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mindy2.jpg\" alt=\"mindy2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mike Lookinland</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Brandy Bunch” show, Mike played the Bobby Brandy role. He was the youngest boy in the family and was usually nice and energetic. His natural hair was sandy brown and curly. His hair had to be dyed and straightened to match the rest in the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mike1.jpg\" alt=\"mike1\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mike has played in a number of shows like “Little House on The Prairie” and other Brandy Bunch specials and movies such as the Towering Inferno before leaving the show world entirely. He is now married and has two kids with a flourishing concrete business in Utah.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-250\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mike2.jpg\" alt=\"mike2\" width=\"583\" height=\"328\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Robbie Rist</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the last 6 episodes of “The Brandy Bunch” show, he joined as Cousin Oliver. Rist was actually 9 even though he played as 8-year old Oliver. He came into the show to help in boosting the ratings due to completion from “Sanford &amp; Son” show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-253\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robbie.jpg\" alt=\"robbie\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Rist provides voiceover as an adult in various films including the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and other animated shows like the “Batman: The Animated Series.” Film soundtracks for movies like Sharknado and Sharknado 2 are some of his talented works. He also performs as a guitarist, lead singer, drummer and/or bassist of a number Los Angeles rock bands.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-254\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robbie2.jpg\" alt=\"robbie2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Robby Benson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known for his film work, Robby was also a star in the TV. He played in show like the “Search for Tomorrow” soap opera and films like Jory, Jeremy, and Ode to Billy Joe, which was a hit. Robby was forced to learn skating so as to play in his famous Ice Castles film.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-255\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robby1.jpg\" alt=\"robby1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – thanks to the Disney film Beauty and The Beast, Robby is now known as the voice of the ‘Beast’. He has served as a professor in Utah, New York, South Carolina, and Indiana. He has had around 4 heart surgeries, but he never wanted to discuss the condition with his producers and directors.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-256\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robby2.jpg\" alt=\"robby2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Helen Hunt</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-216\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/hellen1.jpg\" alt=\"hellen1\" width=\"603\" height=\"327\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Helen has never dropped the ball. She is always in movies and TV. Her Oscar-winning performance in the As Good As It Gets is one of her recent films. She had her own hit comedy Ride, back in 2014. During the 911New York attack, she witnessed the ordeal from her apartment. She moved out three days later to Connecticut.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-217\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/hellen2.jpg\" alt=\"hellen2\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Paolillo</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you have ever watched “Welcome Back Kotter”, then you know Arnold Horshack. He played as a group’s clown in a class of high school kids known as the Sweathogs. He went ahead to perfect his character and learned to love like a hyena.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-259\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ronp1.jpg\" alt=\"ronp1\" width=\"580\" height=\"290\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – in his adult life, Ron was highly demanded. He played a variety of characters for various TV shows and films including “Laverne and Shirley in The Army,” and Friday The Thirteenth among others. He has directed a number of Broadway plays and musicals. He is a fashion designer and wrote a couple of children books. He passed on in 2012 due to a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-260\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ronp2.jpg\" alt=\"Actor Ron Palillo, best known as Arnold Horshack.\" width=\"543\" height=\"305\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Susan Dey</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, Susan played Laurie Partridge. She was joined by Shirley Jones and David Cassidy and other actors to make up the cast for the show. Before joining the cast, Dey was a fashion model. Before the show, she had no acting experience.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-263\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/susan.jpg\" alt=\"Photo of David CASSIDY and PARTRIDGE FAMILY\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Dey has been involved in many films including Skyjacked, Disappearance, and Little Women. She has played in various television shows including “L.A.Law.” She refuses the joining of the Partridge Family Reunion and to date, she and Cassidy never speak after their romantic encounter went horrible.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-264\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/susan2.jpg\" alt=\"susan2\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Murphy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the popular television series “Bewitched”, made Erin very famous. The series ran from 1964 to 1972. In the early seasons, she played young Tabitha Stephens with Diane, her fraternal twin sister. Erin later took the role herself as the kids grew less alike. She became one of the most famous actresses in the world.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after the end of “Bewitched”, Erin bounced to various auditions, turning down various commercials and modeling jobs. The family later moved to Orange County, and she attended 6th grade here. She married and got her first kid at 21 years. She loved acting, and this led her into teaching the craft. Whenever film shooting was in town, she would work in makeup and production. Her stunt double role for Melissa Leo and Virginia Madsen was great. 10 years later, she went back to Los Angeles and began working on reality TV shows, celebrity judge, and commercials. She owns two companies, and one of them sells frozen vodka martini ice pops. She is married and mother of 6 boys.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Karen Carpenter</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Karen plunged into fame as a drummer and singer. Her skill on the instrument was an admiration for many. Luminaries would go on to love her style. Her massive success in the 70s came thanks to her contralto vocal range. Together with Richard, her brother, they had various performances. Her “Close to You” album featured various singles that peaked in the Hot 100.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she passed away European tour where The Carpenters were to perform for Queen Elizabeth. She was involved in performances up until her death.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Barry Williams</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the hit series “The Brady Bunch”, Barry played the role of Greg Brady, the eldest child. Her career was flourished and soon after, he became a love for many female fans across the United States. He also recorded 4 albums and together with his TV siblings, the fame came calling.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Barry scooped the Young Artist Foundation Former Child Star Lifetime Achievement Award in 1989. Three years later, the honor was followed by releasing an autobiography, Growing Up Brady…I Was A Teenage Greg. It remained in the list of best-seller for3 months. In 2001, as an executive producer, he turned his book into a made-for-TV movie on NBC. He recently held a guest role in “Brady Bunch” specials and other shows like “That 70’s Show” and “Three’s Company”. Barry spent a good time in the musical theater for roles like in “The Sound of Music,” “West Side Story,” and “Grease.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Maureen McCormick</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Maureen was the leading lady for “The Brady Bunch” show. She is best known for the role played in the show as Marcia Brady between 1969 and 1974.she was Brady’s oldest girl. She portrayed a smart, pretty, and confident girl that was popular in school and home. She was a politics’ enthusiast. Her iconic role came when she was 12 years old.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she married Michael Cummings and got a daughter in 1989, Natalie. After the end of her TV life, she struggled with drug addiction but eventually overcame it. She appeared as a contestant in the “VH1’s Celebrity Fit Club” and won in 2007.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Scott Baio</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the former heart-throb teen is popularly known for his role in the “Happy Days” show as Chachi. He was the love interest for Joanie Cunningham (Erin Moran). He played as the leading the musical gangster film called “Bugsy Malone”. The child actors in the film gave it a great twist. Jodie Foster, one of the actors; won the future Academy winner. Baio had beaten over 2,000 kids for this part.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Scott later joined “Joanie Loves Chachi”, a spin-off show after his “Happy Days” time. He later played in other films like Skatetown USA, Zapped, and Foxes among others. He has recently starred in his own reality show. He produces shows for Nick at Nite. He is a registered Republican and was reported to be in an altercation with a barista for failing to name the 2016 Republican presumptive nominee.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Danny Bonaduce</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the 70s, Danny rose as a child actor to fame. He played as Danny Partridge in the famous “The Partridge Family.” His bright-red hair and the great ways as a child in the family band bought his name. He was the group’s fictional bass guitar player. In the show, he Danny costarred with David Cassidy. They have remained friends since the first show.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he is now a television and radio personality, professional wrestler, and comedian.  He starred in a number of TV series after the show ended. Some of the series include “Breaking Bonaduce”, a VH1’s reality show back in 205. He hosted radio shows in Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Danny has also been a regular music and talk show host at a Seattle radio known as KZOK-FM as from November 2011.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Tatum O’Neal</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – her stats says it all: she won the 1974 Academy Award while at the age of 10. Her turn as Addie Loggins in the Paper Moon made her take home the golden statue. In 1976, she made an appearance in The Bad News Bears and also Nickelodeon the same year. She left a lasting mark in Hollywood.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she got married in 1986 to John McErnroe and got three kids. They divorced in 1994 after separating in 1992. She had a flourishing career in the film industry back in the ‘70s. However, things changed and for the next 15 years, she would only appear in 5 films. Her guest appearance on “8 Simple Rules for Dating My Teenage Daughter” marked her return to the film world in the 2000s. She also appeared in “Law and Order: Criminal Intent” as well as the “Sex and the City.” In 2005, she got a recurring role in the “Rescue Me” hit series. She has gone ahead acting while focusing on her TV shows work.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Linda Blair</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she is mostly known for her tricks to vomit pea soup after spinning her head around in circles. Her role in The Exorcist came at 14 years of age. In The Exorcist II: The Heretic, she decided to renew her role as a posse child in 1977. Her Academy Award nomination was thanks to her first role. She won the Golden Globe. She began as a child model at 6 years. Her short-lived daytime soap opera role in the “Hidden Fences” helped to boost her career.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Blair appeared in various horror, and other low-budget exploitation films in the 1980s such films included Hell Night, Savage Streets, and Chained Heat. Later in 1990, her appearance in the Repossessed comedy she made fun of her horror movie roots. In 1996, she made a cameo in the film Scream. She later appeared in the “L.A. 7” BBC TV show and “Grease”. She hosted the “Scariest Places on Earth” by Fox Family between 2000 and 2006. Her guest role in the ”Supernatural” TV show was her recent one.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Melissa Gilbert</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Melissa started her career in the late ‘60sand early ‘70s. She did a number of commercials before starring as a guest in various TV roles. During her role as Laura Ingalls Wilder in the “Little House on the Prairie”, she had a big breakthrough. This was between 1974 and 1984. She also appeared in various TV movies such as The Miracle Worker as well as The Diary of Anne Frank.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Melissa has continued acting appearing in various TV programs. “Batman: The Animated Series” is one of her well-known roles wither her voice. From 2001 and 2005, she acted as the President of the Screen Actors Guild. In the “Little House of the Prairie, the Musical”, she played Caroline “Ma” Ingalls. She is loved by her fans and when she contested for hit reality TV show, “Dancing with the Stars”, on NBC it was great for her fans. Some health issues forced her to drop from the Michigan US Congress Democratic race in 2016.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Valerie Bertinelli</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Valerie was born in 1960, and by 1975 she had made a name for herself. She had already started appearing in the “One Day at a Time”, a new sitcom. She appeared in the series’ 208 of the 209 episodes before it came to an end in 1984. In 2005, she reunited with the rest of the show’s cast for the “One Day at a Time Reunion Special.” In 1981, she scooped the Golden Globe at 21 years of age.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Valerie’s career hasn’t shown any signs to slow down. She has been acting all along. She starred in 2 of the ‘90s sitcoms “Café Americain” and “Sydney.” She joined “Touched by an Angel” show that lasted 2 seasons. She later became Jenny Craig’s spokesperson after struggling with her weight for long. She appeared in many commercials for the diet company. She later joined Betty White, Jane Leeves, and Wendie Malick for the TV Land series “Hot in Cleveland” in 2010. The series lasted until June 3 2015.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mackenzie Phillips</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – when she worked on the American Graffiti hit, Mackenzie was only 12. Her stardom continued in the 1970s with her Julie Cooper role in the “One Day at a Time” TV series. By then, she was taking home $50,000 a week. She started doing drugs and drinking by the third season leading to late arrivals on the TV show. She was forced into taking a 6-week break and later entered the Fair Oaks Hospital for treatment. In 1981, she was invited by the producers of the “One Day at a Time” back into the show. She collapsed into the show’s set after getting back into cocaine addiction. She was fired for good.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she checked into rehabilitation for long-term in 1992. She remained here for close to 9 months. Later, she co-starred in the Disney Channel series with Cara DeLizia in 1999. It was called “So Weird” playing a fictional rock star Molly Phillips. During her time in the “ER,” “Without a Trace,” “Cold Case,” and “7th Heaven”, she was a guest star. She later became a rehab counselor to help others at the Breathe Life Healing Center in West Hollywood, California.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Kristy McNichol</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – McNichol began her young career in commercials and then into guest appearances in some series like “Starsky &amp; Hutch,” “Love American Style” and “The Bionic Woman” as well as “The Love Boat.” Her Patricia Apple role in the “Apple’s Way” series was her first regular series job. The 1976 “Family” drama series saw her earn the Emmy Awards for Best Supporting Actress in a Dramatic Series. Later, she went into music and recorded the Kristy &amp; Jimmy McNichol album for RCA Records. “He’s So Fine” hit was her best and it peaked at #70.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – her role in the Little Darlings movie continued to make a name for her. She co-starred with Matt Dillon, Cynthia Dixon, and Tatum O’Neal. Alongside Dennis Quaid and Mark Hamill, she appeared in The Night the Lights Went Out in Georgia. A year later, Kristy would appear in Only When I Laugh by Neil Simon. She was then nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress. Before leaving the cast of “Empty Nest”, Kristy appeared in several seasons but returned for the final episode in 1995. She has left the screen since then but continues to voice characters in various animated series like “Invasion America” and “Extreme Ghostbusters.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Adam Rich</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Rich is best known for the television series “Eight Is Enough.” He played as Nicholas Bradford, the youngest son. It ran from 1977 to 81 for five seasons. His bowl haircut was an inspiration to many parents who did the same for their kids.it was one of his recognizable aspects. He was known as “America’s little brother” for this iconic role. He had a rough encounter in the ‘80s, and he went under for good.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at 14, Rich had started smoking Marijuana. Things went even worse at 17 when he dropped out of high school. He almost lost his life to Valium overdose in 1989. His pharmacy burglar attempt in 1991 got him arrested. 5 years later, Might – a San Francisco-based magazine – published a death hoax through his consent claiming to have been murdered. In 2001, he was arrested for driving under the influence. He has entered and left the rehab for at least 3 times. Currently, he is shopping around for new TV films and shows’ script ideas.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Tanya Tucker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at just 13 years of age, this kid shot into the country charts thanks to her “Delta Dawn” hit. Mel Tillis was the first one to discover her. This was through a stage invitation thanks to her vocal skills. In 1969, her family moved to Las Vegas and not long before she was regularly performing in the city. She gained Dolores Fuller’s attention and later signed to Colombia Records.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Tanya had a successful career. Decades after her first hit, she became one of the most successful country singers of all time. She collected a streak of Top 10 and Top 40 hits. Her country music prowess saw her get nominated for various Country Music Association awards. She released various albums that were popular.  Some of her hits included “Blood Red and Goin’ Down” and “What’s Your Mama’s Name?” of 1973. 2 years later, another hit came by: “Lizzie and Rainman.” It was later followed by the “Strong Enough to Bend” in 1988. She is arguably one of the few childhood stars to carry their fans into adulthood stardom. She has been reckoned as a top influence in the female country music world.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Danielle Spencer</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Danielle played the part of Dee Thomas in the “What’s Happening” television show. In the cast, she played as the “more than annoying little sister” and did so with aplomb. She is famously known for her favorite saying: “Ooooohh, I’m tellin’ Mama!” The show lasted from August 1976 to April 1979.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Spencer is now a doctor of b=veterinary medicine in California. In 2014, she was diagnosed with breast cancer but she was lucky to beat it. She is the only kid actor to be inducted into the Smithsonian Museum as a permanent exhibition on African American Culture.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Moran</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the television show “Happy Days”, Erin played the youngest child of the Cunningham family. She played Joanie Cunningham with a sense of timing and comedy skills that were considered perfect for a “brat sister.” She played this part from 1974 to 1984 and later from 1982 to 1983 during the spin-off “Joanie Loves Chachi.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after “Happy Days”, she played sporadic roles. She would later get into financial issues. Things went south when Moran’s downward took to a spiral and the world watched her drink in public. She was evicted from their house and forced to move into a trailer with her mother-in-law and husband.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Lance Kerwin</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you are familiar with Salem’s Lot, “The Family Holvak,” and “James at Fifteen (and Sixteen),” then you know who Lance Kerwin. He played all of them with other 20 more roles in television and film in the 70s. As a child star, Kerwin played in his show of the decade “Emergency” and in 1979, he played his last: Salem’s Lot.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Kerwin retired in 1995 after a successful acting career. He worked as a minister in Kaua’i, Hawaii. He still lies there. Lance had admitted to having smoked pot before his 10th birthday. He was a crack user at his 20s. He had to go through a number of rehab stints. He got clean, and his wife pledged guilty to fraud. It was later discovered that he had falsified papers to get food stamps. He had around 3 homes in the USA.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Leif Garrett</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – like David Cassidy, Leif was a brilliant child actor, TV personality, and singer.Leif started the ‘70s with a bang: the film Walking Tall was the opener and drew the curtains with Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. He made appearances in at least 10 films and TV shows. He impressed everyone he worked with. In the late 70s, his personal difficulties.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – it is true to say that Leif’s downfall was crafted by his partying, drugs and celebrity life. At 17, he crashed a leased Porsche 1979, leaving his friend a paraplegic. He has been in and out of drug and legal troubles. He has been arrested for heroin possession and once bought cocaine from undercover cops. His adult life has been marred by controversy and drama. He was ordered for rehab.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mason Reese</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his look and talent were Mason’s perfect recipe for his stardom in the 70s. He acted in 70 TV commercials alone. He was ever on shows such as “Mike Douglas” and “Howard Cosell.” He was literally on almost every talk show back then. He lived as a pop star back in the days.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mason became a restaurateur after his TV retirement. He opened a number of restaurants like Paladar and Destination Bar and Grille in the area of Manhattan. He has been raising money to make the pending “Life Interrupted” TV pilot. The show featured Dan Wells, who played in “Gilligan’s Island” as Mary Ann; Alison Arngrim, who played Neil Oleson in ”Little House on the Prairie;” Erin Murphy, who played Tabitha on “Bewitched;” and Michael Learned, who played Olivia Walton in “The Waltons;” as well as “The Brady Bunch’s” Robbie Rich, who played Cousin Oliver among other television icons.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mark Lester</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known by US fans thanks to his Oliver Twist’s character, Lester made his film debut at 6 years. During the musical adaption of the film, he took the role of Oliver at 8 years. He could never sing, so all his singing was dubbed by musical director’s daughter in the Oliver Twist.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at the age of 19 Lester retired from acting and went to school. He went to be an osteopath. He was a close friend of Michael Jackson, and they became Godfathers to each other’s children. There claims that he gave sperm to Michael Jackson to conceive and the chances are that the children are his biologically.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Haywood Nelson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his Dwayne Nelson role in the “What’s Happening!!” series made him so popular. The series aired between 1976 and 1979. He starred in the spin-off series “What’s Happening Now!!” from1985 to 1988. As a child, Nelson appeared in various national commercials and later in the movie Mixed Company. In 1974, alongside Mario Thomas, Nelson appeared on Broadway in Thieves. He starred in “Sanford and Son” at 14 years as Grady’s grandson. He later starred in the “Grady”, a spin-off of “Sanford and Son.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Nelson had difficulties landing another TV show of such a national appeal. However, he has continued to work in TV. He guest-starred in the “Kojak” before he went to work behind the scenes. He has been recently working with talk shows’ crew, TV shows, and interview programs. He is among the first African American teen idols to be nationally recognized.<!--nextpage--></h3>','Top Child Stars of the 70s - Now and Then','','inherit','closed','closed','','199-revision-v1','','','2016-12-01 15:01:29','2016-12-01 15:01:29','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/2016/12/01/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(274,2,'2016-12-01 15:15:40','2016-12-01 15:15:40','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Jodie Foster</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at 3 years, Jodie had begun her acting career. At 5 years, she made her way into the TV series “Mayberry R.F.D.” she had become a regular fixture of the primetime TV by the late 1960s. She starred in a number of children films. In her teens, she had a breakout and made appearances in The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, Taxi Driver, and Disney’s Freaky Friday, and Candleshoe.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-223 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie1.jpg\" alt=\"jodie1\" width=\"659\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – her Hollywood life continued to flourish. She decided to attend Yale and appeared in the controversial The Accused film. She won the Academy Award and Golden Globe. 3 years later, she took home another Oscar thanks to her role in The Silence of the Lambs as Claire. She still thrives in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-224 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie2.jpg\" alt=\"jodie2\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n<h3> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Howard</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – back in the days, Ron was prominent for his acting. His role in “The Andy Griffith Show” made him so popular in the 60s. His most successful acting role came through the “Happy Days” show as Richie Cunningham, the lead character. He grew up in Milwaukee as a mild-mannered teenager.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-257 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron1.jpg\" alt=\"ron1\" width=\"592\" height=\"296\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Howard is one of the most successful people in the world of television and film in the Hollywood’s history. To say he has succeeded as an actor, producer, or director is not enough. He has been in over 27 files, directed over 28 motion picture films and produced close to 20 other films. He has truly lived to his potential.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-258\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron2.jpg\" alt=\"ron2\" width=\"656\" height=\"328\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Kim Richards</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she starred in a number of shows and films through the 70s. She was one the most popular child actors around. She seemed to be all over the public eye with her role in films like Escape to Witch Mountain and its Return from Witch Mountain sequel and shows like “Nanny and the Professor” and “James at Sixteen.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-229 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim1.jpg\" alt=\"kim1\" width=\"597\" height=\"336\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – in 2010, Kim came back into the public and was part of the hit reality series “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills” together with her sister Kyle. There was a rumor of drugs and alcohol abuse soon after starting the show. This was rumored to be partly due to her erratic behavior on camera. Her tribulations went on back in 2015 when she was arrested for public intoxication, trespassing, battery on a police officer and resisting an officer at the Beverly Hills Hotel. She now returns to the show as guest star occasionally.</h3>\r\n<h3> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-230 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim2.jpg\" alt=\"kim2\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>The Jacksons</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – remember the “Jackson Five”? The hit group was made of Jackie, Jermaine, Marlon, Michael, and Tito. Their first 4 singles shot to the billboard charts as number one setting a record in the music business back in 1970. The singles were “I Want You Back,” “ABC,” “The Love You Save,” and “I’ll Be There.” The 4 songs were released over 9 months and “I’ll Be There” maintained at the top for 5 weeks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-219 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson1.jpg\" alt=\"jackson1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – after 17-year hiatus, the Jacksons reunited to celebrate Michael Jackson’s solo career, back in 2011. They had a Unity Tour where they performed. The brothers still perform even though Michael is dead and Randy retired years ago.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-220 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson2.jpg\" alt=\"jackson2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage-->Janet</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Janet is the youngest member of the Jackson family. She performed in a number of shows with her older brothers. She was, however, more into acting than singing. She took the role of Penny in the “Good Ties” show as a kid. She played a battered and frightened child, neighbor to the Evans family. She appeared in “Different Strokes” and “Fame” hit shows but still managed her singing career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-221\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet1.jpg\" alt=\"LOS ANGELES - JANUARY 1: Actresses Janet Jackson (left) and Ja\'net Dubois appear in a scene from the CBS television comedy series &quot;GOOD TIMES&quot; in 1974 in Los Angeles, CA. (Photo by CBS via Getty Images)\" width=\"600\" height=\"439\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Janet has grown to be only second to her brother Michael in the recording industry. She is highly celebrated and sold millions of records. She has starred in hit movies, awarded with multi-platinum albums, and appearing in performances. She is now married to billionaire Wissam Al Mana.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-222\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet2.jpg\" alt=\"162420084SR00004_Sergio_Ros\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Johnny Whitaker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – from “Family Affair” to “General Hospital,” John played in a number of television series. In the Tom Sawyer film, John became the first to give Jodie Foster an on-screen kiss. After the death of his on-screen sister (“Family Affair) Anissa Jones, John had a difficult life and retired from acting for some time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-225\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/johny1.jpg\" alt=\"johny1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – John went through a hard life of substance abuse. His family came to his rescue and his 12-step program cleansed him for over a decade now. He can fluently speak Spanish, Portuguese, French and American Sign Language.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-226\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/johny2.jpg\" alt=\"johny2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>David Cassidy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, David starred as Keith Partridge. Keith was the lead singer in the family band. He was hired solely for his good looks. In reality, the show producers never cared whether or not he could sing.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-209\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/David-cassidy-then.jpg\" alt=\"david-cassidy-then\" width=\"600\" height=\"303\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he lived on to prove to the producers that he could sing. This went on, and David produced ten albums with The Partridge Family. This saw the plunge of David into superstardom. He has a successful career in music and television.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-204\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/cassidy1.jpg\" alt=\"cassidy1\" width=\"594\" height=\"297\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mindy Cohn</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Her Natalie portrayal made her so popular. She was an irrepressible “Facts of Life” series’ student back in 1979to 1988. The show’s success is argued to be on Natalie’s character. In some way, this role ‘cursed’ her television role: she could never get a new one.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-251\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mindy1.jpg\" alt=\"mindy1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she earned a Cultural Anthropology degree while still acting. She is a founder of the weSPARK cancer support center. She makes guest television appearances but majorly on voiceover. The “Velma” if the “Scooby-Doo” animation series is her famous voice. She was nominated for Emmy for her work.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-252\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mindy2.jpg\" alt=\"mindy2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mike Lookinland</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Brandy Bunch” show, Mike played the Bobby Brandy role. He was the youngest boy in the family and was usually nice and energetic. His natural hair was sandy brown and curly. His hair had to be dyed and straightened to match the rest in the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mike1.jpg\" alt=\"mike1\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mike has played in a number of shows like “Little House on The Prairie” and other Brandy Bunch specials and movies such as the Towering Inferno before leaving the show world entirely. He is now married and has two kids with a flourishing concrete business in Utah.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-250\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mike2.jpg\" alt=\"mike2\" width=\"583\" height=\"328\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Robbie Rist</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the last 6 episodes of “The Brandy Bunch” show, he joined as Cousin Oliver. Rist was actually 9 even though he played as 8-year old Oliver. He came into the show to help in boosting the ratings due to completion from “Sanford &amp; Son” show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-253\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robbie.jpg\" alt=\"robbie\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Rist provides voiceover as an adult in various films including the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and other animated shows like the “Batman: The Animated Series.” Film soundtracks for movies like Sharknado and Sharknado 2 are some of his talented works. He also performs as a guitarist, lead singer, drummer and/or bassist of a number Los Angeles rock bands.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-254\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robbie2.jpg\" alt=\"robbie2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Robby Benson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known for his film work, Robby was also a star in the TV. He played in show like the “Search for Tomorrow” soap opera and films like Jory, Jeremy, and Ode to Billy Joe, which was a hit. Robby was forced to learn skating so as to play in his famous Ice Castles film.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-255\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robby1.jpg\" alt=\"robby1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – thanks to the Disney film Beauty and The Beast, Robby is now known as the voice of the ‘Beast’. He has served as a professor in Utah, New York, South Carolina, and Indiana. He has had around 4 heart surgeries, but he never wanted to discuss the condition with his producers and directors.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-256\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robby2.jpg\" alt=\"robby2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Helen Hunt</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-216\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/hellen1.jpg\" alt=\"hellen1\" width=\"603\" height=\"327\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Helen has never dropped the ball. She is always in movies and TV. Her Oscar-winning performance in the As Good As It Gets is one of her recent films. She had her own hit comedy Ride, back in 2014. During the 911New York attack, she witnessed the ordeal from her apartment. She moved out three days later to Connecticut.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-217\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/hellen2.jpg\" alt=\"hellen2\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Paolillo</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you have ever watched “Welcome Back Kotter”, then you know Arnold Horshack. He played as a group’s clown in a class of high school kids known as the Sweathogs. He went ahead to perfect his character and learned to love like a hyena.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-259\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ronp1.jpg\" alt=\"ronp1\" width=\"580\" height=\"290\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – in his adult life, Ron was highly demanded. He played a variety of characters for various TV shows and films including “Laverne and Shirley in The Army,” and Friday The Thirteenth among others. He has directed a number of Broadway plays and musicals. He is a fashion designer and wrote a couple of children books. He passed on in 2012 due to a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-260\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ronp2.jpg\" alt=\"Actor Ron Palillo, best known as Arnold Horshack.\" width=\"543\" height=\"305\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Susan Dey</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, Susan played Laurie Partridge. She was joined by Shirley Jones and David Cassidy and other actors to make up the cast for the show. Before joining the cast, Dey was a fashion model. Before the show, she had no acting experience.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-263\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/susan.jpg\" alt=\"Photo of David CASSIDY and PARTRIDGE FAMILY\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Dey has been involved in many films including Skyjacked, Disappearance, and Little Women. She has played in various television shows including “L.A.Law.” She refuses the joining of the Partridge Family Reunion and to date, she and Cassidy never speak after their romantic encounter went horrible.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-264\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/susan2.jpg\" alt=\"susan2\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Murphy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the popular television series “Bewitched”, made Erin very famous. The series ran from 1964 to 1972. In the early seasons, she played young Tabitha Stephens with Diane, her fraternal twin sister. Erin later took the role herself as the kids grew less alike. She became one of the most famous actresses in the world.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-212\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/erin1.jpg\" alt=\"erin1\" width=\"506\" height=\"380\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after the end of “Bewitched”, Erin bounced to various auditions, turning down various commercials and modeling jobs. The family later moved to Orange County, and she attended 6th grade here. She married and got her first kid at 21 years. She loved acting, and this led her into teaching the craft. Whenever film shooting was in town, she would work in makeup and production. Her stunt double role for Melissa Leo and Virginia Madsen was great. 10 years later, she went back to Los Angeles and began working on reality TV shows, celebrity judge, and commercials. She owns two companies, and one of them sells frozen vodka martini ice pops. She is married and mother of 6 boys.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-213\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Erin2.jpg\" alt=\"erin2\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Karen Carpenter</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Karen plunged into fame as a drummer and singer. Her skill on the instrument was an admiration for many. Luminaries would go on to love her style. Her massive success in the 70s came thanks to her contralto vocal range. Together with Richard, her brother, they had various performances. Her “Close to You” album featured various singles that peaked in the Hot 100.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-227\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/karen1.jpg\" alt=\"karen1\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she passed away European tour where The Carpenters were to perform for Queen Elizabeth. She was involved in performances up until her death.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-228\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/karen2.jpg\" alt=\"karen2\" width=\"642\" height=\"331\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Barry Williams</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the hit series “The Brady Bunch”, Barry played the role of Greg Brady, the eldest child. Her career was flourished and soon after, he became a love for many female fans across the United States. He also recorded 4 albums and together with his TV siblings, the fame came calling.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Barry scooped the Young Artist Foundation Former Child Star Lifetime Achievement Award in 1989. Three years later, the honor was followed by releasing an autobiography, Growing Up Brady…I Was A Teenage Greg. It remained in the list of best-seller for3 months. In 2001, as an executive producer, he turned his book into a made-for-TV movie on NBC. He recently held a guest role in “Brady Bunch” specials and other shows like “That 70’s Show” and “Three’s Company”. Barry spent a good time in the musical theater for roles like in “The Sound of Music,” “West Side Story,” and “Grease.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Maureen McCormick</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Maureen was the leading lady for “The Brady Bunch” show. She is best known for the role played in the show as Marcia Brady between 1969 and 1974.she was Brady’s oldest girl. She portrayed a smart, pretty, and confident girl that was popular in school and home. She was a politics’ enthusiast. Her iconic role came when she was 12 years old.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she married Michael Cummings and got a daughter in 1989, Natalie. After the end of her TV life, she struggled with drug addiction but eventually overcame it. She appeared as a contestant in the “VH1’s Celebrity Fit Club” and won in 2007.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Scott Baio</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the former heart-throb teen is popularly known for his role in the “Happy Days” show as Chachi. He was the love interest for Joanie Cunningham (Erin Moran). He played as the leading the musical gangster film called “Bugsy Malone”. The child actors in the film gave it a great twist. Jodie Foster, one of the actors; won the future Academy winner. Baio had beaten over 2,000 kids for this part.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Scott later joined “Joanie Loves Chachi”, a spin-off show after his “Happy Days” time. He later played in other films like Skatetown USA, Zapped, and Foxes among others. He has recently starred in his own reality show. He produces shows for Nick at Nite. He is a registered Republican and was reported to be in an altercation with a barista for failing to name the 2016 Republican presumptive nominee.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Danny Bonaduce</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the 70s, Danny rose as a child actor to fame. He played as Danny Partridge in the famous “The Partridge Family.” His bright-red hair and the great ways as a child in the family band bought his name. He was the group’s fictional bass guitar player. In the show, he Danny costarred with David Cassidy. They have remained friends since the first show.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he is now a television and radio personality, professional wrestler, and comedian.  He starred in a number of TV series after the show ended. Some of the series include “Breaking Bonaduce”, a VH1’s reality show back in 205. He hosted radio shows in Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Danny has also been a regular music and talk show host at a Seattle radio known as KZOK-FM as from November 2011.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Tatum O’Neal</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – her stats says it all: she won the 1974 Academy Award while at the age of 10. Her turn as Addie Loggins in the Paper Moon made her take home the golden statue. In 1976, she made an appearance in The Bad News Bears and also Nickelodeon the same year. She left a lasting mark in Hollywood.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she got married in 1986 to John McErnroe and got three kids. They divorced in 1994 after separating in 1992. She had a flourishing career in the film industry back in the ‘70s. However, things changed and for the next 15 years, she would only appear in 5 films. Her guest appearance on “8 Simple Rules for Dating My Teenage Daughter” marked her return to the film world in the 2000s. She also appeared in “Law and Order: Criminal Intent” as well as the “Sex and the City.” In 2005, she got a recurring role in the “Rescue Me” hit series. She has gone ahead acting while focusing on her TV shows work.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Linda Blair</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she is mostly known for her tricks to vomit pea soup after spinning her head around in circles. Her role in The Exorcist came at 14 years of age. In The Exorcist II: The Heretic, she decided to renew her role as a posse child in 1977. Her Academy Award nomination was thanks to her first role. She won the Golden Globe. She began as a child model at 6 years. Her short-lived daytime soap opera role in the “Hidden Fences” helped to boost her career.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Blair appeared in various horror, and other low-budget exploitation films in the 1980s such films included Hell Night, Savage Streets, and Chained Heat. Later in 1990, her appearance in the Repossessed comedy she made fun of her horror movie roots. In 1996, she made a cameo in the film Scream. She later appeared in the “L.A. 7” BBC TV show and “Grease”. She hosted the “Scariest Places on Earth” by Fox Family between 2000 and 2006. Her guest role in the ”Supernatural” TV show was her recent one.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Melissa Gilbert</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Melissa started her career in the late ‘60sand early ‘70s. She did a number of commercials before starring as a guest in various TV roles. During her role as Laura Ingalls Wilder in the “Little House on the Prairie”, she had a big breakthrough. This was between 1974 and 1984. She also appeared in various TV movies such as The Miracle Worker as well as The Diary of Anne Frank.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Melissa has continued acting appearing in various TV programs. “Batman: The Animated Series” is one of her well-known roles wither her voice. From 2001 and 2005, she acted as the President of the Screen Actors Guild. In the “Little House of the Prairie, the Musical”, she played Caroline “Ma” Ingalls. She is loved by her fans and when she contested for hit reality TV show, “Dancing with the Stars”, on NBC it was great for her fans. Some health issues forced her to drop from the Michigan US Congress Democratic race in 2016.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Valerie Bertinelli</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Valerie was born in 1960, and by 1975 she had made a name for herself. She had already started appearing in the “One Day at a Time”, a new sitcom. She appeared in the series’ 208 of the 209 episodes before it came to an end in 1984. In 2005, she reunited with the rest of the show’s cast for the “One Day at a Time Reunion Special.” In 1981, she scooped the Golden Globe at 21 years of age.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Valerie’s career hasn’t shown any signs to slow down. She has been acting all along. She starred in 2 of the ‘90s sitcoms “Café Americain” and “Sydney.” She joined “Touched by an Angel” show that lasted 2 seasons. She later became Jenny Craig’s spokesperson after struggling with her weight for long. She appeared in many commercials for the diet company. She later joined Betty White, Jane Leeves, and Wendie Malick for the TV Land series “Hot in Cleveland” in 2010. The series lasted until June 3 2015.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mackenzie Phillips</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – when she worked on the American Graffiti hit, Mackenzie was only 12. Her stardom continued in the 1970s with her Julie Cooper role in the “One Day at a Time” TV series. By then, she was taking home $50,000 a week. She started doing drugs and drinking by the third season leading to late arrivals on the TV show. She was forced into taking a 6-week break and later entered the Fair Oaks Hospital for treatment. In 1981, she was invited by the producers of the “One Day at a Time” back into the show. She collapsed into the show’s set after getting back into cocaine addiction. She was fired for good.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she checked into rehabilitation for long-term in 1992. She remained here for close to 9 months. Later, she co-starred in the Disney Channel series with Cara DeLizia in 1999. It was called “So Weird” playing a fictional rock star Molly Phillips. During her time in the “ER,” “Without a Trace,” “Cold Case,” and “7th Heaven”, she was a guest star. She later became a rehab counselor to help others at the Breathe Life Healing Center in West Hollywood, California.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Kristy McNichol</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – McNichol began her young career in commercials and then into guest appearances in some series like “Starsky &amp; Hutch,” “Love American Style” and “The Bionic Woman” as well as “The Love Boat.” Her Patricia Apple role in the “Apple’s Way” series was her first regular series job. The 1976 “Family” drama series saw her earn the Emmy Awards for Best Supporting Actress in a Dramatic Series. Later, she went into music and recorded the Kristy &amp; Jimmy McNichol album for RCA Records. “He’s So Fine” hit was her best and it peaked at #70.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – her role in the Little Darlings movie continued to make a name for her. She co-starred with Matt Dillon, Cynthia Dixon, and Tatum O’Neal. Alongside Dennis Quaid and Mark Hamill, she appeared in The Night the Lights Went Out in Georgia. A year later, Kristy would appear in Only When I Laugh by Neil Simon. She was then nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress. Before leaving the cast of “Empty Nest”, Kristy appeared in several seasons but returned for the final episode in 1995. She has left the screen since then but continues to voice characters in various animated series like “Invasion America” and “Extreme Ghostbusters.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Adam Rich</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Rich is best known for the television series “Eight Is Enough.” He played as Nicholas Bradford, the youngest son. It ran from 1977 to 81 for five seasons. His bowl haircut was an inspiration to many parents who did the same for their kids.it was one of his recognizable aspects. He was known as “America’s little brother” for this iconic role. He had a rough encounter in the ‘80s, and he went under for good.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at 14, Rich had started smoking Marijuana. Things went even worse at 17 when he dropped out of high school. He almost lost his life to Valium overdose in 1989. His pharmacy burglar attempt in 1991 got him arrested. 5 years later, Might – a San Francisco-based magazine – published a death hoax through his consent claiming to have been murdered. In 2001, he was arrested for driving under the influence. He has entered and left the rehab for at least 3 times. Currently, he is shopping around for new TV films and shows’ script ideas.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Tanya Tucker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at just 13 years of age, this kid shot into the country charts thanks to her “Delta Dawn” hit. Mel Tillis was the first one to discover her. This was through a stage invitation thanks to her vocal skills. In 1969, her family moved to Las Vegas and not long before she was regularly performing in the city. She gained Dolores Fuller’s attention and later signed to Colombia Records.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Tanya had a successful career. Decades after her first hit, she became one of the most successful country singers of all time. She collected a streak of Top 10 and Top 40 hits. Her country music prowess saw her get nominated for various Country Music Association awards. She released various albums that were popular.  Some of her hits included “Blood Red and Goin’ Down” and “What’s Your Mama’s Name?” of 1973. 2 years later, another hit came by: “Lizzie and Rainman.” It was later followed by the “Strong Enough to Bend” in 1988. She is arguably one of the few childhood stars to carry their fans into adulthood stardom. She has been reckoned as a top influence in the female country music world.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Danielle Spencer</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Danielle played the part of Dee Thomas in the “What’s Happening” television show. In the cast, she played as the “more than annoying little sister” and did so with aplomb. She is famously known for her favorite saying: “Ooooohh, I’m tellin’ Mama!” The show lasted from August 1976 to April 1979.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Spencer is now a doctor of b=veterinary medicine in California. In 2014, she was diagnosed with breast cancer but she was lucky to beat it. She is the only kid actor to be inducted into the Smithsonian Museum as a permanent exhibition on African American Culture.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Moran</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the television show “Happy Days”, Erin played the youngest child of the Cunningham family. She played Joanie Cunningham with a sense of timing and comedy skills that were considered perfect for a “brat sister.” She played this part from 1974 to 1984 and later from 1982 to 1983 during the spin-off “Joanie Loves Chachi.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after “Happy Days”, she played sporadic roles. She would later get into financial issues. Things went south when Moran’s downward took to a spiral and the world watched her drink in public. She was evicted from their house and forced to move into a trailer with her mother-in-law and husband.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Lance Kerwin</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you are familiar with Salem’s Lot, “The Family Holvak,” and “James at Fifteen (and Sixteen),” then you know who Lance Kerwin. He played all of them with other 20 more roles in television and film in the 70s. As a child star, Kerwin played in his show of the decade “Emergency” and in 1979, he played his last: Salem’s Lot.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Kerwin retired in 1995 after a successful acting career. He worked as a minister in Kaua’i, Hawaii. He still lies there. Lance had admitted to having smoked pot before his 10th birthday. He was a crack user at his 20s. He had to go through a number of rehab stints. He got clean, and his wife pledged guilty to fraud. It was later discovered that he had falsified papers to get food stamps. He had around 3 homes in the USA.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Leif Garrett</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – like David Cassidy, Leif was a brilliant child actor, TV personality, and singer.Leif started the ‘70s with a bang: the film Walking Tall was the opener and drew the curtains with Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. He made appearances in at least 10 films and TV shows. He impressed everyone he worked with. In the late 70s, his personal difficulties.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – it is true to say that Leif’s downfall was crafted by his partying, drugs and celebrity life. At 17, he crashed a leased Porsche 1979, leaving his friend a paraplegic. He has been in and out of drug and legal troubles. He has been arrested for heroin possession and once bought cocaine from undercover cops. His adult life has been marred by controversy and drama. He was ordered for rehab.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mason Reese</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his look and talent were Mason’s perfect recipe for his stardom in the 70s. He acted in 70 TV commercials alone. He was ever on shows such as “Mike Douglas” and “Howard Cosell.” He was literally on almost every talk show back then. He lived as a pop star back in the days.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mason became a restaurateur after his TV retirement. He opened a number of restaurants like Paladar and Destination Bar and Grille in the area of Manhattan. He has been raising money to make the pending “Life Interrupted” TV pilot. The show featured Dan Wells, who played in “Gilligan’s Island” as Mary Ann; Alison Arngrim, who played Neil Oleson in ”Little House on the Prairie;” Erin Murphy, who played Tabitha on “Bewitched;” and Michael Learned, who played Olivia Walton in “The Waltons;” as well as “The Brady Bunch’s” Robbie Rich, who played Cousin Oliver among other television icons.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mark Lester</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known by US fans thanks to his Oliver Twist’s character, Lester made his film debut at 6 years. During the musical adaption of the film, he took the role of Oliver at 8 years. He could never sing, so all his singing was dubbed by musical director’s daughter in the Oliver Twist.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at the age of 19 Lester retired from acting and went to school. He went to be an osteopath. He was a close friend of Michael Jackson, and they became Godfathers to each other’s children. There claims that he gave sperm to Michael Jackson to conceive and the chances are that the children are his biologically.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Haywood Nelson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his Dwayne Nelson role in the “What’s Happening!!” series made him so popular. The series aired between 1976 and 1979. He starred in the spin-off series “What’s Happening Now!!” from1985 to 1988. As a child, Nelson appeared in various national commercials and later in the movie Mixed Company. In 1974, alongside Mario Thomas, Nelson appeared on Broadway in Thieves. He starred in “Sanford and Son” at 14 years as Grady’s grandson. He later starred in the “Grady”, a spin-off of “Sanford and Son.”<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Nelson had difficulties landing another TV show of such a national appeal. However, he has continued to work in TV. He guest-starred in the “Kojak” before he went to work behind the scenes. He has been recently working with talk shows’ crew, TV shows, and interview programs. He is among the first African American teen idols to be nationally recognized.<!--nextpage--></h3>','Top Child Stars of the 70s - Now and Then','','inherit','closed','closed','','199-revision-v1','','','2016-12-01 15:15:40','2016-12-01 15:15:40','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/2016/12/01/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(275,1,'2016-12-01 15:42:05','2016-12-01 15:42:05','[vc_row el_class=\"td-grid-what\"][vc_column][td_block_big_grid_4 category_id=\"\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][td_block_trending_now category_id=\"\" sort=\"random_posts\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][td_block_5 custom_title=\"\" sort=\"random_posts\" limit=\"3\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][td_block_ad_box spot_id=\"custom_ad_1\" spot_title=\"- Advertisement -\"][vc_empty_space height=\"16px\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"td-ss-row\"][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][td_block_23 custom_title=\"\" category_id=\"\" sort=\"random_posts\" limit=\"3\"][vc_empty_space height=\"20px\"][td_block_12 custom_title=\"\" sort=\"random_posts\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][td_block_5 custom_title=\"\" sort=\"random_posts\" limit=\"3\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][td_block_ad_box spot_id=\"custom_ad_1\" spot_title=\"- Advertisement -\"][vc_empty_space height=\"16px\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','25-revision-v1','','','2016-12-01 15:42:05','2016-12-01 15:42:05','',25,'http://35.163.51.132/2016/12/01/25-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(276,2,'2016-12-01 17:03:36','2016-12-01 17:03:36','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Jodie Foster</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at 3 years, Jodie had begun her acting career. At 5 years, she made her way into the TV series “Mayberry R.F.D.” she had become a regular fixture of the primetime TV by the late 1960s. She starred in a number of children films. In her teens, she had a breakout and made appearances in The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, Taxi Driver, and Disney’s Freaky Friday, and Candleshoe.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-223 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie1.jpg\" alt=\"jodie1\" width=\"659\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – her Hollywood life continued to flourish. She decided to attend Yale and appeared in the controversial The Accused film. She won the Academy Award and Golden Globe. 3 years later, she took home another Oscar thanks to her role in The Silence of the Lambs as Claire. She still thrives in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-224 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Jodie2.jpg\" alt=\"jodie2\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n<h3> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Howard</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – back in the days, Ron was prominent for his acting. His role in “The Andy Griffith Show” made him so popular in the 60s. His most successful acting role came through the “Happy Days” show as Richie Cunningham, the lead character. He grew up in Milwaukee as a mild-mannered teenager.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-257 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron1.jpg\" alt=\"ron1\" width=\"592\" height=\"296\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Howard is one of the most successful people in the world of television and film in the Hollywood’s history. To say he has succeeded as an actor, producer, or director is not enough. He has been in over 27 files, directed over 28 motion picture films and produced close to 20 other films. He has truly lived to his potential.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-258\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ron2.jpg\" alt=\"ron2\" width=\"656\" height=\"328\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Kim Richards</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she starred in a number of shows and films through the 70s. She was one the most popular child actors around. She seemed to be all over the public eye with her role in films like Escape to Witch Mountain and its Return from Witch Mountain sequel and shows like “Nanny and the Professor” and “James at Sixteen.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-229 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim1.jpg\" alt=\"kim1\" width=\"597\" height=\"336\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – in 2010, Kim came back into the public and was part of the hit reality series “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills” together with her sister Kyle. There was a rumor of drugs and alcohol abuse soon after starting the show. This was rumored to be partly due to her erratic behavior on camera. Her tribulations went on back in 2015 when she was arrested for public intoxication, trespassing, battery on a police officer and resisting an officer at the Beverly Hills Hotel. She now returns to the show as guest star occasionally.</h3>\r\n<h3> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-230 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kim2.jpg\" alt=\"kim2\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>The Jacksons</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – remember the “Jackson Five”? The hit group was made of Jackie, Jermaine, Marlon, Michael, and Tito. Their first 4 singles shot to the billboard charts as number one setting a record in the music business back in 1970. The singles were “I Want You Back,” “ABC,” “The Love You Save,” and “I’ll Be There.” The 4 songs were released over 9 months and “I’ll Be There” maintained at the top for 5 weeks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-219 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson1.jpg\" alt=\"jackson1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Now – after 17-year hiatus, the Jacksons reunited to celebrate Michael Jackson’s solo career, back in 2011. They had a Unity Tour where they performed. The brothers still perform even though Michael is dead and Randy retired years ago.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-220 alignleft\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/jackson2.jpg\" alt=\"jackson2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage-->Janet</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Janet is the youngest member of the Jackson family. She performed in a number of shows with her older brothers. She was, however, more into acting than singing. She took the role of Penny in the “Good Ties” show as a kid. She played a battered and frightened child, neighbor to the Evans family. She appeared in “Different Strokes” and “Fame” hit shows but still managed her singing career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-221\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet1.jpg\" alt=\"LOS ANGELES - JANUARY 1: Actresses Janet Jackson (left) and Ja\'net Dubois appear in a scene from the CBS television comedy series &quot;GOOD TIMES&quot; in 1974 in Los Angeles, CA. (Photo by CBS via Getty Images)\" width=\"600\" height=\"439\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Janet has grown to be only second to her brother Michael in the recording industry. She is highly celebrated and sold millions of records. She has starred in hit movies, awarded with multi-platinum albums, and appearing in performances. She is now married to billionaire Wissam Al Mana.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-222\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/janet2.jpg\" alt=\"162420084SR00004_Sergio_Ros\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3>Johnny Whitaker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – from “Family Affair” to “General Hospital,” John played in a number of television series. In the Tom Sawyer film, John became the first to give Jodie Foster an on-screen kiss. After the death of his on-screen sister (“Family Affair) Anissa Jones, John had a difficult life and retired from acting for some time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-225\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/johny1.jpg\" alt=\"johny1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – John went through a hard life of substance abuse. His family came to his rescue and his 12-step program cleansed him for over a decade now. He can fluently speak Spanish, Portuguese, French and American Sign Language.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-226\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/johny2.jpg\" alt=\"johny2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>David Cassidy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, David starred as Keith Partridge. Keith was the lead singer in the family band. He was hired solely for his good looks. In reality, the show producers never cared whether or not he could sing.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-209\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/David-cassidy-then.jpg\" alt=\"david-cassidy-then\" width=\"600\" height=\"303\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he lived on to prove to the producers that he could sing. This went on, and David produced ten albums with The Partridge Family. This saw the plunge of David into superstardom. He has a successful career in music and television.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-204\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/cassidy1.jpg\" alt=\"cassidy1\" width=\"594\" height=\"297\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mindy Cohn</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Her Natalie portrayal made her so popular. She was an irrepressible “Facts of Life” series’ student back in 1979to 1988. The show’s success is argued to be on Natalie’s character. In some way, this role ‘cursed’ her television role: she could never get a new one.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-251\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mindy1.jpg\" alt=\"mindy1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she earned a Cultural Anthropology degree while still acting. She is a founder of the weSPARK cancer support center. She makes guest television appearances but majorly on voiceover. The “Velma” if the “Scooby-Doo” animation series is her famous voice. She was nominated for Emmy for her work.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-252\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mindy2.jpg\" alt=\"mindy2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mike Lookinland</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Brandy Bunch” show, Mike played the Bobby Brandy role. He was the youngest boy in the family and was usually nice and energetic. His natural hair was sandy brown and curly. His hair had to be dyed and straightened to match the rest in the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mike1.jpg\" alt=\"mike1\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mike has played in a number of shows like “Little House on The Prairie” and other Brandy Bunch specials and movies such as the Towering Inferno before leaving the show world entirely. He is now married and has two kids with a flourishing concrete business in Utah.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-250\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/mike2.jpg\" alt=\"mike2\" width=\"583\" height=\"328\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Robbie Rist</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the last 6 episodes of “The Brandy Bunch” show, he joined as Cousin Oliver. Rist was actually 9 even though he played as 8-year old Oliver. He came into the show to help in boosting the ratings due to completion from “Sanford &amp; Son” show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-253\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robbie.jpg\" alt=\"robbie\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Rist provides voiceover as an adult in various films including the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and other animated shows like the “Batman: The Animated Series.” Film soundtracks for movies like Sharknado and Sharknado 2 are some of his talented works. He also performs as a guitarist, lead singer, drummer and/or bassist of a number Los Angeles rock bands.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-254\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robbie2.jpg\" alt=\"robbie2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Robby Benson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known for his film work, Robby was also a star in the TV. He played in show like the “Search for Tomorrow” soap opera and films like Jory, Jeremy, and Ode to Billy Joe, which was a hit. Robby was forced to learn skating so as to play in his famous Ice Castles film.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-255\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robby1.jpg\" alt=\"robby1\" width=\"604\" height=\"302\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – thanks to the Disney film Beauty and The Beast, Robby is now known as the voice of the ‘Beast’. He has served as a professor in Utah, New York, South Carolina, and Indiana. He has had around 4 heart surgeries, but he never wanted to discuss the condition with his producers and directors.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-256\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/robby2.jpg\" alt=\"robby2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Helen Hunt</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-216\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/hellen1.jpg\" alt=\"hellen1\" width=\"603\" height=\"327\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Helen has never dropped the ball. She is always in movies and TV. Her Oscar-winning performance in the As Good As It Gets is one of her recent films. She had her own hit comedy Ride, back in 2014. During the 911New York attack, she witnessed the ordeal from her apartment. She moved out three days later to Connecticut.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-217\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/hellen2.jpg\" alt=\"hellen2\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Ron Paolillo</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you have ever watched “Welcome Back Kotter”, then you know Arnold Horshack. He played as a group’s clown in a class of high school kids known as the Sweathogs. He went ahead to perfect his character and learned to love like a hyena.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-259\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ronp1.jpg\" alt=\"ronp1\" width=\"580\" height=\"290\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – in his adult life, Ron was highly demanded. He played a variety of characters for various TV shows and films including “Laverne and Shirley in The Army,” and Friday The Thirteenth among others. He has directed a number of Broadway plays and musicals. He is a fashion designer and wrote a couple of children books. He passed on in 2012 due to a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-260\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ronp2.jpg\" alt=\"Actor Ron Palillo, best known as Arnold Horshack.\" width=\"543\" height=\"305\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Susan Dey</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in “The Partridge Family” hit show, Susan played Laurie Partridge. She was joined by Shirley Jones and David Cassidy and other actors to make up the cast for the show. Before joining the cast, Dey was a fashion model. Before the show, she had no acting experience.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-263\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/susan.jpg\" alt=\"Photo of David CASSIDY and PARTRIDGE FAMILY\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Dey has been involved in many films including Skyjacked, Disappearance, and Little Women. She has played in various television shows including “L.A.Law.” She refuses the joining of the Partridge Family Reunion and to date, she and Cassidy never speak after their romantic encounter went horrible.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-264\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/susan2.jpg\" alt=\"susan2\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Murphy</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the popular television series “Bewitched”, made Erin very famous. The series ran from 1964 to 1972. In the early seasons, she played young Tabitha Stephens with Diane, her fraternal twin sister. Erin later took the role herself as the kids grew less alike. She became one of the most famous actresses in the world.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-212\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/erin1.jpg\" alt=\"erin1\" width=\"506\" height=\"380\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after the end of “Bewitched”, Erin bounced to various auditions, turning down various commercials and modeling jobs. The family later moved to Orange County, and she attended 6th grade here. She married and got her first kid at 21 years. She loved acting, and this led her into teaching the craft. Whenever film shooting was in town, she would work in makeup and production. Her stunt double role for Melissa Leo and Virginia Madsen was great. 10 years later, she went back to Los Angeles and began working on reality TV shows, celebrity judge, and commercials. She owns two companies, and one of them sells frozen vodka martini ice pops. She is married and mother of 6 boys.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-213\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Erin2.jpg\" alt=\"erin2\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Karen Carpenter</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Karen plunged into fame as a drummer and singer. Her skill on the instrument was an admiration for many. Luminaries would go on to love her style. Her massive success in the 70s came thanks to her contralto vocal range. Together with Richard, her brother, they had various performances. Her “Close to You” album featured various singles that peaked in the Hot 100.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-227\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/karen1.jpg\" alt=\"karen1\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she passed away European tour where The Carpenters were to perform for Queen Elizabeth. She was involved in performances up until her death.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-228\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/karen2.jpg\" alt=\"karen2\" width=\"642\" height=\"331\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Barry Williams</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the hit series “The Brady Bunch”, Barry played the role of Greg Brady, the eldest child. Her career was flourished and soon after, he became a love for many female fans across the United States. He also recorded 4 albums and together with his TV siblings, the fame came calling.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-202\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/barry1.jpg\" alt=\"barry1\" width=\"594\" height=\"433\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Barry scooped the Young Artist Foundation Former Child Star Lifetime Achievement Award in 1989. Three years later, the honor was followed by releasing an autobiography, Growing Up Brady…I Was A Teenage Greg. It remained in the list of best-seller for3 months. In 2001, as an executive producer, he turned his book into a made-for-TV movie on NBC. He recently held a guest role in “Brady Bunch” specials and other shows like “That 70’s Show” and “Three’s Company”. Barry spent a good time in the musical theater for roles like in “The Sound of Music,” “West Side Story,” and “Grease.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-203\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/barry2.jpg\" alt=\"3 23 2013 WATN-Barry Williams\" width=\"551\" height=\"368\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Maureen McCormick</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Maureen was the leading lady for “The Brady Bunch” show. She is best known for the role played in the show as Marcia Brady between 1969 and 1974.she was Brady’s oldest girl. She portrayed a smart, pretty, and confident girl that was popular in school and home. She was a politics’ enthusiast. Her iconic role came when she was 12 years old.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-245\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Maureen1.jpg\" alt=\"maureen1\" width=\"593\" height=\"444\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she married Michael Cummings and got a daughter in 1989, Natalie. After the end of her TV life, she struggled with drug addiction but eventually overcame it. She appeared as a contestant in the “VH1’s Celebrity Fit Club” and won in 2007.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-246\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Maureen2.jpg\" alt=\"maureen2\" width=\"598\" height=\"379\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Scott Baio</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – the former heart-throb teen is popularly known for his role in the “Happy Days” show as Chachi. He was the love interest for Joanie Cunningham (Erin Moran). He played as the leading the musical gangster film called “Bugsy Malone”. The child actors in the film gave it a great twist. Jodie Foster, one of the actors; won the future Academy winner. Baio had beaten over 2,000 kids for this part.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-261\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/scot1.jpg\" alt=\"scot1\" width=\"601\" height=\"398\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Scott later joined “Joanie Loves Chachi”, a spin-off show after his “Happy Days” time. He later played in other films like Skatetown USA, Zapped, and Foxes among others. He has recently starred in his own reality show. He produces shows for Nick at Nite. He is a registered Republican and was reported to be in an altercation with a barista for failing to name the 2016 Republican presumptive nominee.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-262\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/scot2.jpg\" alt=\"scot2\" width=\"565\" height=\"381\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Danny Bonaduce</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the 70s, Danny rose as a child actor to fame. He played as Danny Partridge in the famous “The Partridge Family.” His bright-red hair and the great ways as a child in the family band bought his name. He was the group’s fictional bass guitar player. In the show, he Danny costarred with David Cassidy. They have remained friends since the first show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-207\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Danny1.jpg\" alt=\"danny1\" width=\"596\" height=\"418\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – he is now a television and radio personality, professional wrestler, and comedian.  He starred in a number of TV series after the show ended. Some of the series include “Breaking Bonaduce”, a VH1’s reality show back in 205. He hosted radio shows in Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Danny has also been a regular music and talk show host at a Seattle radio known as KZOK-FM as from November 2011.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-208\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Danny2.jpg\" alt=\"danny2\" width=\"480\" height=\"419\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Tatum O’Neal</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – her stats says it all: she won the 1974 Academy Award while at the age of 10. Her turn as Addie Loggins in the Paper Moon made her take home the golden statue. In 1976, she made an appearance in The Bad News Bears and also Nickelodeon the same year. She left a lasting mark in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-267\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tatum1.jpg\" alt=\"tatum1\" width=\"597\" height=\"398\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she got married in 1986 to John McErnroe and got three kids. They divorced in 1994 after separating in 1992. She had a flourishing career in the film industry back in the ‘70s. However, things changed and for the next 15 years, she would only appear in 5 films. Her guest appearance on “8 Simple Rules for Dating My Teenage Daughter” marked her return to the film world in the 2000s. She also appeared in “Law and Order: Criminal Intent” as well as the “Sex and the City.” In 2005, she got a recurring role in the “Rescue Me” hit series. She has gone ahead acting while focusing on her TV shows work.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-268\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tatum2.jpg\" alt=\"tatum2\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Linda Blair</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – she is mostly known for her tricks to vomit pea soup after spinning her head around in circles. Her role in The Exorcist came at 14 years of age. In The Exorcist II: The Heretic, she decided to renew her role as a posse child in 1977. Her Academy Award nomination was thanks to her first role. She won the Golden Globe. She began as a child model at 6 years. Her short-lived daytime soap opera role in the “Hidden Fences” helped to boost her career.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-237\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Linda1.gif\" alt=\"linda1\" width=\"513\" height=\"405\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Blair appeared in various horror, and other low-budget exploitation films in the 1980s such films included Hell Night, Savage Streets, and Chained Heat. Later in 1990, her appearance in the Repossessed comedy she made fun of her horror movie roots. In 1996, she made a cameo in the film Scream. She later appeared in the “L.A. 7” BBC TV show and “Grease”. She hosted the “Scariest Places on Earth” by Fox Family between 2000 and 2006. Her guest role in the ”Supernatural” TV show was her recent one.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-238\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Linda2.jpg\" alt=\"LINDA BLAIR\" width=\"498\" height=\"374\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Melissa Gilbert</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Melissa started her career in the late ‘60sand early ‘70s. She did a number of commercials before starring as a guest in various TV roles. During her role as Laura Ingalls Wilder in the “Little House on the Prairie”, she had a big breakthrough. This was between 1974 and 1984. She also appeared in various TV movies such as The Miracle Worker as well as The Diary of Anne Frank.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-247\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Melissa1.jpg\" alt=\"melissa1\" width=\"605\" height=\"318\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Melissa has continued acting appearing in various TV programs. “Batman: The Animated Series” is one of her well-known roles wither her voice. From 2001 and 2005, she acted as the President of the Screen Actors Guild. In the “Little House of the Prairie, the Musical”, she played Caroline “Ma” Ingalls. She is loved by her fans and when she contested for hit reality TV show, “Dancing with the Stars”, on NBC it was great for her fans. Some health issues forced her to drop from the Michigan US Congress Democratic race in 2016.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-248\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Melissa2.jpg\" alt=\"melissa2\" width=\"602\" height=\"339\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Valerie Bertinelli</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Valerie was born in 1960, and by 1975 she had made a name for herself. She had already started appearing in the “One Day at a Time”, a new sitcom. She appeared in the series’ 208 of the 209 episodes before it came to an end in 1984. In 2005, she reunited with the rest of the show’s cast for the “One Day at a Time Reunion Special.” In 1981, she scooped the Golden Globe at 21 years of age.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-269\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Valerie1.jpg\" alt=\"valerie1\" width=\"481\" height=\"362\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Valerie’s career hasn’t shown any signs to slow down. She has been acting all along. She starred in 2 of the ‘90s sitcoms “Café Americain” and “Sydney.” She joined “Touched by an Angel” show that lasted 2 seasons. She later became Jenny Craig’s spokesperson after struggling with her weight for long. She appeared in many commercials for the diet company. She later joined Betty White, Jane Leeves, and Wendie Malick for the TV Land series “Hot in Cleveland” in 2010. The series lasted until June 3 2015.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-270\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Valerie2.jpg\" alt=\"valerie2\" width=\"597\" height=\"399\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mackenzie Phillips</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – when she worked on the American Graffiti hit, Mackenzie was only 12. Her stardom continued in the 1970s with her Julie Cooper role in the “One Day at a Time” TV series. By then, she was taking home $50,000 a week. She started doing drugs and drinking by the third season leading to late arrivals on the TV show. She was forced into taking a 6-week break and later entered the Fair Oaks Hospital for treatment. In 1981, she was invited by the producers of the “One Day at a Time” back into the show. She collapsed into the show’s set after getting back into cocaine addiction. She was fired for good.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-239\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mackenzie1.jpg\" alt=\"mackenzie1\" width=\"598\" height=\"337\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – she checked into rehabilitation for long-term in 1992. She remained here for close to 9 months. Later, she co-starred in the Disney Channel series with Cara DeLizia in 1999. It was called “So Weird” playing a fictional rock star Molly Phillips. During her time in the “ER,” “Without a Trace,” “Cold Case,” and “7th Heaven”, she was a guest star. She later became a rehab counselor to help others at the Breathe Life Healing Center in West Hollywood, California.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-240\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mackenzie2.jpg\" alt=\"mackenzie2\" width=\"602\" height=\"294\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Kristy McNichol</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – McNichol began her young career in commercials and then into guest appearances in some series like “Starsky &amp; Hutch,” “Love American Style” and “The Bionic Woman” as well as “The Love Boat.” Her Patricia Apple role in the “Apple’s Way” series was her first regular series job. The 1976 “Family” drama series saw her earn the Emmy Awards for Best Supporting Actress in a Dramatic Series. Later, she went into music and recorded the Kristy &amp; Jimmy McNichol album for RCA Records. “He’s So Fine” hit was her best and it peaked at #70.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-231\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Kristy1.jpg\" alt=\"kristy1\" width=\"602\" height=\"339\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – her role in the Little Darlings movie continued to make a name for her. She co-starred with Matt Dillon, Cynthia Dixon, and Tatum O’Neal. Alongside Dennis Quaid and Mark Hamill, she appeared in The Night the Lights Went Out in Georgia. A year later, Kristy would appear in Only When I Laugh by Neil Simon. She was then nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress. Before leaving the cast of “Empty Nest”, Kristy appeared in several seasons but returned for the final episode in 1995. She has left the screen since then but continues to voice characters in various animated series like “Invasion America” and “Extreme Ghostbusters.”</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-232\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Kristy2.jpg\" alt=\"kristy2\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Adam Rich</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Rich is best known for the television series “Eight Is Enough.” He played as Nicholas Bradford, the youngest son. It ran from 1977 to 81 for five seasons. His bowl haircut was an inspiration to many parents who did the same for their kids.it was one of his recognizable aspects. He was known as “America’s little brother” for this iconic role. He had a rough encounter in the ‘80s, and he went under for good.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-200\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Adam1.jpg\" alt=\"adam1\" width=\"601\" height=\"460\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at 14, Rich had started smoking Marijuana. Things went even worse at 17 when he dropped out of high school. He almost lost his life to Valium overdose in 1989. His pharmacy burglar attempt in 1991 got him arrested. 5 years later, Might – a San Francisco-based magazine – published a death hoax through his consent claiming to have been murdered. In 2001, he was arrested for driving under the influence. He has entered and left the rehab for at least 3 times. Currently, he is shopping around for new TV films and shows’ script ideas.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-201\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Adam2.jpg\" alt=\"adam2\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Tanya Tucker</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – at just 13 years of age, this kid shot into the country charts thanks to her “Delta Dawn” hit. Mel Tillis was the first one to discover her. This was through a stage invitation thanks to her vocal skills. In 1969, her family moved to Las Vegas and not long before she was regularly performing in the city. She gained Dolores Fuller’s attention and later signed to Colombia Records.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-265\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tanya1.jpg\" alt=\"tanya1\" width=\"599\" height=\"337\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Tanya had a successful career. Decades after her first hit, she became one of the most successful country singers of all time. She collected a streak of Top 10 and Top 40 hits. Her country music prowess saw her get nominated for various Country Music Association awards. She released various albums that were popular.  Some of her hits included “Blood Red and Goin’ Down” and “What’s Your Mama’s Name?” of 1973. 2 years later, another hit came by: “Lizzie and Rainman.” It was later followed by the “Strong Enough to Bend” in 1988. She is arguably one of the few childhood stars to carry their fans into adulthood stardom. She has been reckoned as a top influence in the female country music world.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-266\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tanya2.jpg\" alt=\"tanya2\" width=\"595\" height=\"335\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Danielle Spencer</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – Danielle played the part of Dee Thomas in the “What’s Happening” television show. In the cast, she played as the “more than annoying little sister” and did so with aplomb. She is famously known for her favorite saying: “Ooooohh, I’m tellin’ Mama!” The show lasted from August 1976 to April 1979.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-205\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Danielle1.jpg\" alt=\"danielle1\" width=\"598\" height=\"299\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Spencer is now a doctor of b=veterinary medicine in California. In 2014, she was diagnosed with breast cancer but she was lucky to beat it. She is the only kid actor to be inducted into the Smithsonian Museum as a permanent exhibition on African American Culture.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-206\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Danielle2.jpg\" alt=\"danielle2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Erin Moran</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – in the television show “Happy Days”, Erin played the youngest child of the Cunningham family. She played Joanie Cunningham with a sense of timing and comedy skills that were considered perfect for a “brat sister.” She played this part from 1974 to 1984 and later from 1982 to 1983 during the spin-off “Joanie Loves Chachi.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-210\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Erin-Moran1.jpg\" alt=\"7731_0036\" width=\"574\" height=\"287\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – after “Happy Days”, she played sporadic roles. She would later get into financial issues. Things went south when Moran’s downward took to a spiral and the world watched her drink in public. She was evicted from their house and forced to move into a trailer with her mother-in-law and husband.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-211\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Erin-Moran2.jpg\" alt=\"erin-moran2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Lance Kerwin</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – if you are familiar with Salem’s Lot, “The Family Holvak,” and “James at Fifteen (and Sixteen),” then you know who Lance Kerwin. He played all of them with other 20 more roles in television and film in the 70s. As a child star, Kerwin played in his show of the decade “Emergency” and in 1979, he played his last: Salem’s Lot.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-233\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Lance1.jpg\" alt=\"lance1\" width=\"602\" height=\"301\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Kerwin retired in 1995 after a successful acting career. He worked as a minister in Kaua’i, Hawaii. He still lies there. Lance had admitted to having smoked pot before his 10th birthday. He was a crack user at his 20s. He had to go through a number of rehab stints. He got clean, and his wife pledged guilty to fraud. It was later discovered that he had falsified papers to get food stamps. He had around 3 homes in the USA.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-234\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Lance2.jpg\" alt=\"lance2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Leif Garrett</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – like David Cassidy, Leif was a brilliant child actor, TV personality, and singer.Leif started the ‘70s with a bang: the film Walking Tall was the opener and drew the curtains with Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. He made appearances in at least 10 films and TV shows. He impressed everyone he worked with. In the late 70s, his personal difficulties.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-235\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Leif1.jpg\" alt=\"leif1\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – it is true to say that Leif’s downfall was crafted by his partying, drugs and celebrity life. At 17, he crashed a leased Porsche 1979, leaving his friend a paraplegic. He has been in and out of drug and legal troubles. He has been arrested for heroin possession and once bought cocaine from undercover cops. His adult life has been marred by controversy and drama. He was ordered for rehab.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-236\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Leif2.jpg\" alt=\"leif2\" width=\"598\" height=\"337\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mason Reese</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his look and talent were Mason’s perfect recipe for his stardom in the 70s. He acted in 70 TV commercials alone. He was ever on shows such as “Mike Douglas” and “Howard Cosell.” He was literally on almost every talk show back then. He lived as a pop star back in the days.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-243\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mason1.jpg\" alt=\"mason1\" width=\"602\" height=\"301\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Mason became a restaurateur after his TV retirement. He opened a number of restaurants like Paladar and Destination Bar and Grille in the area of Manhattan. He has been raising money to make the pending “Life Interrupted” TV pilot. The show featured Dan Wells, who played in “Gilligan’s Island” as Mary Ann; Alison Arngrim, who played Neil Oleson in ”Little House on the Prairie;” Erin Murphy, who played Tabitha on “Bewitched;” and Michael Learned, who played Olivia Walton in “The Waltons;” as well as “The Brady Bunch’s” Robbie Rich, who played Cousin Oliver among other television icons.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-244\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mason2.jpg\" alt=\"mason2\" width=\"588\" height=\"294\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Mark Lester</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – best known by US fans thanks to his Oliver Twist’s character, Lester made his film debut at 6 years. During the musical adaption of the film, he took the role of Oliver at 8 years. He could never sing, so all his singing was dubbed by musical director’s daughter in the Oliver Twist.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-241\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mark1.jpg\" alt=\"mark1\" width=\"602\" height=\"482\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – at the age of 19 Lester retired from acting and went to school. He went to be an osteopath. He was a close friend of Michael Jackson, and they became Godfathers to each other’s children. There claims that he gave sperm to Michael Jackson to conceive and the chances are that the children are his biologically.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-242\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mark2.jpg\" alt=\"mark2\" width=\"601\" height=\"601\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Haywood Nelson</h3>\r\n<h3>Then – his Dwayne Nelson role in the “What’s Happening!!” series made him so popular. The series aired between 1976 and 1979. He starred in the spin-off series “What’s Happening Now!!” from1985 to 1988. As a child, Nelson appeared in various national commercials and later in the movie Mixed Company. In 1974, alongside Mario Thomas, Nelson appeared on Broadway in Thieves. He starred in “Sanford and Son” at 14 years as Grady’s grandson. He later starred in the “Grady”, a spin-off of “Sanford and Son.”</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-214\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Haywood1.jpg\" alt=\"haywood1\" width=\"598\" height=\"415\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h3>Now – Nelson had difficulties landing another TV show of such a national appeal. However, he has continued to work in TV. He guest-starred in the “Kojak” before he went to work behind the scenes. He has been recently working with talk shows’ crew, TV shows, and interview programs. He is among the first African American teen idols to be nationally recognized.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-215\" src=\"http://35.163.51.132/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Haywood2.jpg\" alt=\"haywood2\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></h3>\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>','Top Child Stars of the 70s - Now and Then','','inherit','closed','closed','','199-revision-v1','','','2016-12-01 17:03:36','2016-12-01 17:03:36','',199,'http://35.163.51.132/2016/12/01/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(277,2,'2016-12-01 17:15:13','2016-12-01 17:15:13',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','277','','','2016-12-01 17:15:35','2016-12-01 17:15:35','',0,'http://35.163.51.132/?p=277',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(278,2,'2016-12-01 17:15:13','2016-12-01 17:15:13',' ','','','