INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (595,2,'2016-12-12 18:21:14','2016-12-12 18:21:14','<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">They were once our favorite stars and were the most familiar faces on TV. Those who were children during the 80’s, still allot a special place to these stars. We, however, don’t see them as frequently as before. What happened to them? Some of them left the world of showbiz and now, spend their time in retirement. </span></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Emilio Estevez</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>You might not know but Emilio is actor Charlie Sheen’s elder brother. He worked with stars like Sean Penn, during the 80’s.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-571\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Emilio-Estevez.jpg\" alt=\"emilio-estevez\" width=\"339\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Judd Nelson</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Judd set his mark with “The Breakfast Club”. Prior to that, he acted in Nikita.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-572\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Judd-Nelson.jpg\" alt=\"judd-nelson\" width=\"353\" height=\"353\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Madonna</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>If you ask an 80’s kid about his or her music preference, they are most likely to answer: Madonna.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-573\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Madonna.jpg\" alt=\"madonna\" width=\"345\" height=\"345\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1> <span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Ally Sheedy</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">The Brat Pack star began her journey with the 1983 hit: Bad Boys.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-574\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Ally-Sheedy.jpg\" alt=\"ally-sheedy\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong> </strong><strong>Molly Ringwald</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">The charming redhead gained fame for her role in “Sixteen Candles”.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-575\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Molly-Ringwald.jpg\" alt=\"molly-ringwald\" width=\"345\" height=\"345\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Andrew McCarthy</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Andrew got himself another contract with hit <em>Brat Pack</em> lineup in “Pretty in Pink”.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-576\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Andrew-McCarthy.jpg\" alt=\"andrew-mccarthy\" width=\"356\" height=\"356\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Demi Moore</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Leaving behind her disappointment in school, Moore established herself as one of the most desirable actresses in Hollywood.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-577\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Demi-Moore.jpg\" alt=\"demi-moore\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Ricky Schroder</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>When he was just 12, he played the lead role in the famous TV show Silver Spoons.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-585\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Ricky-Schroder.jpg\" alt=\"ricky-schroder\" width=\"357\" height=\"357\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1> <span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Anthony Michael Hall</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">Anthony got spotlight after appearing in hit comedy “National Lampoon’s Vacation”.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-586\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Anthony-Michael-Hall.jpg\" alt=\"anthony-michael-hall\" width=\"325\" height=\"325\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>George Michael</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">People still remember the English singer for hit tracks like Careless Whisper and Last Christmas.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-594\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/George-Michael.jpg\" alt=\"george-michael\" width=\"336\" height=\"336\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1> <span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Alyssa Milano</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">Alyssa got breakthrough with her performance in ABC sitcom “Who\'s the Boss?”.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-593\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Alyssa-Milano.jpg\" alt=\"alyssa-milano\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Tom Cruise</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">Cruise is still one of the big shots in Hollywood. Many of us don’t know that Cruise began his career with a minor role in the movie “The Outsiders”.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-591\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tom-Cruise.jpg\" alt=\"tom-cruise\" width=\"325\" height=\"325\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>John Cusack</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Cusack entered the world of showbiz with his enthralling performance in “Better Off Dead”.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-592\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/John-Cusack.jpg\" alt=\"john-cusack\" width=\"322\" height=\"322\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Michael J. Fox</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Canadian Michael J. Fox became known for his acting skills with his role in “Family Ties”.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-590\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Michael-J.-Fox.jpg\" alt=\"michael-j-fox\" width=\"328\" height=\"328\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Mr. T</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Anyone who grew up during the 80’s will go WOW if you asked them about “The A-Team”. Indeed the name <strong>Mr. T</strong> became synonymous with the hit show.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-589\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Mr.-T.jpg\" alt=\"mr-t\" width=\"335\" height=\"335\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Matthew Broderick</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Matthew set his footprint with his acting in “Ferris Bueller\'s Day Off”. He eventually made it to some of the biggest hits in Hollywood.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-588\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Matthew-Broderick.jpg\" alt=\"matthew-broderick\" width=\"334\" height=\"334\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Rob Lowe</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">Rob was also a part of “The Outsiders” cast along with Tom Cruise. He also appeared in <em>Brat Pack</em>.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-587\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Rob-Lowe.jpg\" alt=\"rob-lowe\" width=\"329\" height=\"329\" /> <!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Kevin Bacon</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">He became a household name after playing the character of Ren McCormack. Even today he is a regular face in Hollywood movies.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-584\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Kevin-Bacon.jpg\" alt=\"kevin-bacon\" width=\"354\" height=\"354\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Patrick Dempsey</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">The actor became audience favorite after playing a nerdy character in “Can’t Buy Me Love”.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-583\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Patrick-Dempsey.jpg\" alt=\"patrick-dempsey\" width=\"346\" height=\"346\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Cyndi Lauper</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Her first album “She\'s So Unusual” was released in 1983. She eventually established herself as the pop sensation of the decade.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-582\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Cyndi-Lauper.jpg\" alt=\"cyndi-lauper\" width=\"355\" height=\"355\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1> <strong>Matt Dillon</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Bad boy Matt Dillon took part in many 80’s flicks. He was one of the heartthrobs of the decade.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-581\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Matt-Dillon.jpg\" alt=\"matt-dillon\" width=\"374\" height=\"374\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h1><strong>Drew Barrymore</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Successful Hollywood actress Drew Barrymore appeared on television when she was just 11! Her first breakthrough came with <em>E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial.</em></h2>\r\n<h2><em><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-580\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Drew-Barrymore.jpg\" alt=\"drew-barrymore\" width=\"380\" height=\"380\" /><!--nextpage--></em></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Corey Feldman</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">Corey commenced his acting career when he was just 3. He became popular for his performance in “The Goonies”.</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-579\" src=\"http://theladypost.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Corey-Feldman.jpg\" alt=\"corey-feldman\" width=\"370\" height=\"370\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h2>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Debbie Gibson</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000\">Her hit single <em>Foolish Beat </em>hit the top of the Billboard soon after it was released; 